{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 1455827, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "310125", "body": "[b]Normal Mode Strategy[/b]\n\n[b]Phase 1[/b]\nRagnaros is two-tanked, and will put a stacking fire DoT on its current aggro target. Tanks must switch off near 3-4 stacks and use cooldowns towards the end of their turn.\nEvery 30 seconds, Ragnaros will cast Sulfuras Smash. He will face a random player and hit the area they were standing in after two seconds of cast time. The location of the smash is given away by three lava pools formed together on the spot. When the cast is finished, three lava waves will spawn and move in different directions. (one is in the direction the boss was facing, and the other two will be to the perpendicular sides.) The locations of these smashes will always be within an arc just barely past the edge of the platform in front of Ragnaros. They are easily avoidable by standing diagonal to the direction of the smash or close-up to the boss. Touching the lava wave will knock back the player and place a strong magic DoT on them which will kill them if not dispelled immediately.\nRagnaros will also randomly burst the entire raid, knocking them back a few yards. (Similar to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=46753]Al'Akir[/url]'s [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=93261]Wind Burst[/url] but without a cast time.) Players should not be near the edge of the platform or they will get knocked off into the lava. Players must also be aware of this knockback possibly due at the same time a Sulfuras Smash occurs so they do not accidentally get knocked into the lava waves or a trap. [i]This mechanic only occurs during Phase 1.[/i]\nRanged must be fully spread out as a random ranged player will be targeted with a trap on the ground that will damage the entire raid when triggered. It will remain there for the entire fight unless it is activated by a player moving into it. Warlocks with Demonic Portals, Mages with Slowfall, or Priests with Levitate can trigger these without dying. [b]However,[/b] they must be sure the entire raid is topped before doing so as this combined with Ragnaros' random burst will kill someone who is not fully healed.\n\n[b]Phase 1.5[/b]\nAt 70%, Ragnaros will face a random direction in front of him and throw down Sulfuras before submerging. Eight fire elemental adds will spawn in static locations around the perimeter of the platform. If any one of these elementals touches Sulfuras, they will cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=100260]Supernova[/url] and blast your entire raid for a lot of damage. This will wipe your raid if you are not fully topped. They start with a movement speed increase which will decrease as their health lowers to 50%. All melee should be separated to their own assigned add to stunlock and burn it down while ranged finish off all adds prioritized by whichever is closest to Sulfuras. These adds cannot be rooted or snared, but they [b]can[/b] be [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=49576]Death Gripped[/url], and knocked back with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=50516]Typhoon[/url]. When all adds have died or 45 seconds have elapsed in this phase, Ragnaros will reemerge. \n\n[b]Phase 2[/b]\nRagnaros uses a new ability which will also be used in Phase 3. Engulfing Flames will be cast for 3 seconds on a third of the room (separated in lanes: melee, middle, ranged)\nEvery 60 seconds, Ragnaros will spawn lava seeds on random players within the raid. All players must be spread out to avoid the splash damage these seeds cause when placed but remain on one side of the room before they are placed. After all seeds are placed, players must cross over to the other side immediately before these seeds detonate. Damage from all the seeds are based on proximity, so the closer the deadlier. After the explosion, adds will spawn for each one of these seeds and target random players. The raid must stack up to AoE all these adds down before spreading back out for the next wave of seeds. The raid can stack anywhere, but it would be easiest to do so on top of the tank at the very front of the platform to avoid being caught off guard by Sulfuras Smash. However, if any players stagger and are too far back they are likely to get instantly killed by Sulfuras Smash. \n\nThe biggest part of this phase is being in the right place at the right time. When a Sulfuras Smash or Engulfing Flames occurs, players must remain at least 6 yards away from each other when Lava Seeds are coming. These two abilities will also occur when players are stacking up to AoE adds so they must be aware of them coming. The abilities used in this phase are static and sequential, so it's easy to memorize what will happen when. (e.g. Every second lava seed spawn having a Sulfuras Smash happen right after the explosion)\n\n[b]Phase 2.5[/b]\nStarts at 40% HP. The exact same as Phase 1.5 with the addition of two Lava Scions, each one spawning on separate sides of the room which must be tanked. All players must kill their elemental adds quickly as before with the exception of the furthest one to buy time to kill both Lava Scions before Ragnaros reemerges. Chain grips and knockbacks on the last add to use the full duration of the phase while burning down one of the scions to free a tank for Ragnaros in Phase 3. \n\n[b]Phase 3[/b]\nSulfuras Smash and Engulfing Flames are still used in this phase. Very large meteors will now start spawning as a soft enrage in this fight to chase random players. The spawn location is given away with a graphic similar to Hellfire which everyone nearby must move away from. They are extremely slow, and can be knocked back every 5 seconds by doing direct damage to them. However, it should only be hit if it's in danger of touching the player. Meteors do not stay on the same player and may switch to a different one at any time, so it's important to keep distance from all active meteors. Collision with the meteor will cause it to explode, killing the colliding player and everyone within 8 yards. As this phase persists, meteors will keep spawning and chasing more players so Ragnaros must be killed as fast as possible.\n\nAt 10% HP, Ragnaros retreats and awaits you to defeat him on Heroic.\n\n[b]Edit:[/b] Changed tank info & last line.", "date": "2011-06-30T14:53:54-05:00", "rating": 60, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You are wrong about the tank switching...the debuff only lasts 20 seconds, so it's normally done at 3-4 stacks. I don't think it would be feasible to try and live through a 10 stack...the damage would be up to at least 50k a tick.  At the 10% too he doesn't actually die. He merely sinks back into the lava, taking his hammer with him. This is because in heroic, he actually stays and finishes the fight. So for normal, you don't kill him at all, you merely \"set him back\". I didn't notice him actually saying anything when he dies..he runs away without saying a word. I think it would have been cool", "creationdate": "2011-06-30T14:53:55-05:00", "id": 487696, "rating": 21, "commentid": 1455827, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "McEgan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]At 10% HP, Ragnaros dies instantly.[/quote] He doesn't die... It was just [i]too soon. We've come too soon...[/i]", "creationdate": "2011-07-04T12:57:14-05:00", "id": 250076, "rating": 30, "commentid": 1455827, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karlzone", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]At 10% HP, Ragnaros dies instantly. No cutscene, no home-free burn to 0.[/quote]Presumably on H this is when he transitions to the heroic-only extra phase where he walks around the platform and you can kill him for real.  Normal mode was merely a setback.", "creationdate": "2011-07-08T09:33:35-05:00", "id": 251006, "rating": 25, "commentid": 1455827, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Spleener", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote][quote]At 10% HP, Ragnaros dies instantly.[/quote] He doesn't die... It was just too soon. We've come too soon...[/quote]  [quote]Ragnaros: TOO SOON... YOU HAVE COME TOO SOON![/quote]  What are the downraters thinking? NO, Ragnaro doesnt \"die\". It is in fact like what Karlzone have said, we come too soon and he haul ass.", "creationdate": "2011-07-13T22:08:48-05:00", "id": 252200, "rating": 17, "commentid": 1455827, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "anubalabeloralon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's best to stay calm during the last phase- something I haven't been able to do myself. Be alert and don't freak out. Focus on playing volleyball with the meteors while getting Rag's health down~", "creationdate": "2011-10-30T20:06:00-05:00", "id": 274303, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1455827, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "EonLight", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-12T16:23:58-05:00", 3, "310125"]}
