{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 1461322, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Manbewbs", "body": "I will be explaining the 10 man regular mode encounter of this fight, this is an overview of the whole fight but I will cover some tanking tips as it was my job and know it the most.\n\nThe encounter will need 2 tanks minimum for both raid sizes. The enrage timer is 12 minutes. Ragnaros hits hard on tanks.\n\nThe following two abilities will persist throughout the whole fight aside from the two transition phases where he will be submerged.\nSulfuras Smash will happen, an ability that will show up as 3 circles clumped together on the ground, and smash his hammer on the specified location. Getting hit by the direct ability is a one shot. 3 lava waves will spew out from where the hammer hit, much like Sartharion's lava walls except much smaller but faster. The directions that the walls spawn from will be from the tip of the specified location (outwards pointing to the nearest edge of the platform) and the two sides. It will never point towards Ragnaros himself and will always point in the same directions. If you do happen to get hit by the lava walls, it will hit for about moderate damage and apply a dot on you which needs to be dispelled. It is completely avoidable and should be. Also note that the area where he smashed his hammer will have a ground effect AoE which will do some damage.\nAnother ability Ragnaros does is a stacking DoT called Burning Wound on the tank, this is basically a tank swap. Tanks should taunt immediately after their stacks fall off, as it has a 20 second duration. A tip for the pull is to let the main tank use his threat CD's, and once it wears off tank two taunts to maximize TPS. After that both tanks should taunt off each other immediately.\n\nPhase 1: 100%-70%\n\nDuring phase 1 he will cast hand of Ragnaros, knocking back all players in range of him and do a small amount of damage that cannot be avoided unless ranged (don't bother, you'll have to be off the platform completely).\n\nHe will also cast wrath of Ragnaros and blast a random raid member and inflict moderate damage, blasting them backwards. Basically spread out to avoid multiple players getting hit.\n\nThese two abilities are similar to Al'akir's wind burst.\n\nThe key ability in phase 1 that Ragnaros will use is magma trap, but unlike shadow trap on Lich King this trap will need to be activated or else you will have multiple traps on the platform which will make things chaotic in phase 3. The initial cast will look like a orange swirly heading towards the direction (underneath a player) and needs to be avoided. It will also have a ground effect similar to a shadow crash on general Vezax in Ulduar or the trash packs before the last boss in OK.\nWhen the trap gets detonated, it will do moderate damage to the entire raid. Think of a crackle except less deadly but more often.\nThe way you handle these traps before they get overwhelming is to send a capable ranged player to step on these traps to detonate. You do not get any parachute or slow fall of what sort by default, so you must use a class's ability, such as Slow fall from priests, Blink from mages, disengage from hunters, etc. Coordinate with your healers when you do this, a badly timed detonate may cause a lot of strain or a death.\nTanks should use a CD when the trap gets detonated, Shield wall, BH trinket, anything that reduces damage is great as you won't have a chance to use them much unless healers are falling behind.\n\nThe combination of the multiple knock backs, magma traps, and sulfuras smash can be deadly at times, as if you get knocked back into either a trap, smash, or lava wave it can be a bad start.\n\nPhase 1.5: the phase shift\n\nDuring this phase, Ragnaros himself will not do any damage to tanks, and there not be much damage coming out to the raid. This is ideal time to regenerate mana for healers.\n\nRagnaros will once again, smash his hammer on the ground but will not cause any lava waves. You can tell where his hammer is going to be placed from the 8 beams that will be visible, indicating where 8 adds will spawn. He can place his hammer on the left side, center, or middle. You can tell where it will be before he places them. If 2 beams are to the left and 6 to the right, the hammer will be placed on the left. If it is split (4:4) it will be in the center. If 6 beams are to the left and 2 to the right, it will spawn to the right. These adds don't have any threat and dps may wish to dps as they please. These adds are considered elementals and paladins should glyph into holy wrath to stun them because of the following reason.\nWhen the elementals reach the hammer, it will cause about 100k damage and can easily be a wipe. If everyone is at full HP, a wipe can be prevented but don't expect it. Just kill them before they reach the hammer. The key thing about these adds is the lower their HP is, the slower they are until they're at a point where they move like a snail. To prevent any speedy runs to the hammer, stun them as soon as they come out with a long stun, such as Concussion blow, Hammer of Justice, etc. Split up DPS, with 2 on the left, 2 on the right, and your most capable DPS in the center. DK's can death grip them if one's getting dangerously close, and knock backs work, but aren't recommended for the [b]second[/b] transition.\nWhen the adds die, they'll explode but it's best to have melee stick on them and heal through the small damage.\nDo not leave a Son of Flame active as if Ragnaros comes back up and ones still alive he'll instantly wipe the raid.\n\nPhase 2: 70%-40%\n\nRagnaros will emerge again, but this time there will be no more knock backs, and no more traps. Instead introduced are two new mechanics. \n\nThere will be Engulfing Flames, similar to Valiona's engulfing flames which cover one third of the ground towards the end of Theralion's ground phase.\nTanks must always be in melee range or Ragnaros will start casting on you, which is a lot more damage than melee. The engulfing flame makes it hard to stay in melee range. I found the initial flame easy to avoid but died to the ground effect after. If you look closely at the flames, you will see that they are many circles on the ground that makes it, making a long chain of circles of fire. If you stand in between a circle's top and another circle's top, you can just get in enough for melee range. If you have graphics turned on and you are comfortable then you may not need to do this.\nAnother ability he will cast is Molten seeds. These seeds will spawn on players and do moderate AoE damage. Spread out. The key to this is that because when the seeds explode and do damage, the farther away you are the less damage it'll do. Pretty much have all the players spread out on the right and left sides of the whole platform, no one should be standing in the middle. The tricky part about spreading out is that you will sometimes have an engulfing flame right before seeds, making it tricky to spread after the engulfing flames before the seeds. The same goes for Sulfuras Smash's lava walls.\nWhen the seeds blow up, it is a good time to use raid CD's, AMZ is amazing, AM from holy paladins, DG, RC, SLT, and PW:B are all great for this as you will be stacking for when they do. The reason you want to stack is because after the seeds blow up, adds spawn with low HP and they need to be AoE'd down, a tank cannot pick them up as after spawning they fixate on someone. Best for groups with hunters is to stun all the adds and let them go out to AoE. When the stuns wear off hopefully they're all dead.", "date": "2011-07-05T09:55:32-05:00", "rating": 34, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-05T10:18:36-05:00", 2, "Manbewbs"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 1461325, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Manbewbs", "body": "Cont Phase 2-\n\nA good place to stack is right in front of Ragnaros, and the center of the platform as he will still be doing damage to tanks and because either Engulfing Flames or Sulfuras Smash will happen during the time the raid stacks. When Sulfuras Smash happens, just tuck in further into Ragnaros, making sure you're not standing in lava as there's a little gap between him and the hammer.\nAfter they're all dead, rinse and repeat. We found the first and third stack \"phase\" to be Engulfing Flames, and the second one the Smash. We did not get a fourth one so I cannot comment on it, although it's logical it is a Smash.\n\nPhase 2.5: transition phase\n\nExact same as the first transition aside from one new debuff and a new type of add, Blazing Trail, if it's on a player it will leave a fire trail on the ground and if you stand still with the debuff you will be standing in the stacking fire, obviously not good. This fire trail also heals the little elemental adds, thus making them faster and most likely making a wipe. Stand on the edge of the platform and DPS adds from behind to negate the risk of them healing.\nA new type of an add spawns that have a lot more HP (2 million ish I think?) that must be tanked and killed. The second transition is ideal to pop Bloodlust/Heroism to get these adds down, though prioritizing little adds over large ones. They spawn from the black circles (rock formation on the ground all throughout the encounter). Burn them down once the adds are dead.\nThese adds are tauntable and should be to switch off on Burning stacks of Ragnaros through phase 3.\n\nPhase 3: 40%-10%\n\nEngulfing Flames still persist from phase two during phase three. There is a new mechanic introduced again, this time a flaming Meteor. These Living Meteors have a lot of HP and should not be killed. When they spawn a small hellfire will indicate the location. This meteor will fixate on a random member, not the tanks as far as I saw, and follow them. A yellow line will be connecting the player and the meteor, and the player will have a yellow arrow above their head. If this does reach you, you will explode the meteor, one shot anyone near you and yourself, and get blown off. Luckily you can avoid it reaching you by damaging the meteor and it will knock it back from the player that damaged it. Shortly after it will fixate on a different player and start again. You cannot spam knock him back though, as it gets a debuff after you knock it which prevents it from being knocked back for 5 seconds.\nDuring this phase more and more meteors will spawn until you eventually become overwhelmed.\nHealers should hit the boulder themselves with Moonfire, SW:D, Judgement, or Earth Shock.\n\nThat pretty much concludes my in depth explanation for Ragnaros! Have fun and good luck!", "date": "2011-07-05T09:56:05-05:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-05T10:40:41-05:00", 4, "Manbewbs"]}
