{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1461793, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "wastedtime", "body": "I dont know if its been said here already, but can pallys bubble on the living meteors then explode them in a safe place to remove them?", "date": "2011-07-05T18:54:25-05:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "no, the living meteors will switch target when their target becomes immune (iceblock/divine shield), but you can use that to make it travel double it's normal way, before knocking it. We used it on the first meteor cause it luckily was on our mage, So basicly he ran close to the edge of the platform far away from us and like 10 yards before the meteor hit him he iceblock'ed and our hunter knocked the meteor through him off the platform. The meteor will come back, but as long as it's near the edge or off the platform it's not doing much harm.", "creationdate": "2011-07-09T06:34:27-05:00", "id": 251226, "rating": 20, "commentid": 1461793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "godded", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "im not sure why my comment was downrated you most certainly can run into them while bubbled...", "creationdate": "2011-10-27T11:02:14-05:00", "id": 273613, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1461793, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "331693", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 1466914, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Veratus", "body": "Pro tip: Don't feral charge, unless you like dying in a fiery grave!", "date": "2011-07-11T05:53:07-05:00", "rating": 50, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also, while [spell=51690] is normally safe, it has the capability of dropping you where a Sulfuras Smash has left its burning residue. Hop wisely.", "creationdate": "2011-09-22T22:39:36-05:00", "id": 266383, "rating": 13, "commentid": 1466914, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xathien", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 1467100, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rygol", "body": "Fun fact for hunters - Deterrence will deflect the damage from Molten Seed explosions.", "date": "2011-07-11T11:21:55-05:00", "rating": 56, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just to be sure, do you mean the initial impact that creates the Molten Seed, or the eruption of the Molten Elemental from the seed 10 seconds later?", "creationdate": "2011-09-30T12:02:10-05:00", "id": 267923, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1467100, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Eillesthis", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The eruption from the seed 10 seconds after it lands.", "creationdate": "2011-10-03T14:04:26-05:00", "id": 268496, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1467100, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rygol", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It applies to both", "creationdate": "2012-02-13T22:13:08-06:00", "id": 519170, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1467100, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Declaron", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-08-13T09:47:29-05:00", 2, "Rygol"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 1467619, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "danadocus", "body": "This seems to be true for the new ragnaros as well: Ragnaros will always attack players who are in melee range first, regardless of their position on his hatelist.", "date": "2011-07-12T00:34:24-05:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 1468274, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Forumchibi", "body": "Looking for some advice for the 2nd major phase (the one with the molten seeds):\r\n\r\nMy group today tried many different strategies, and yet the Molten Seeds mixed with the other mechanics continued to wipe us and we have yet to see the next transition or the last phase.  In terms of placement, first we tried gathering in a circle around the center using the floor pattern as a guide.  In later attempts we tried stacking on one side of the room and running to the opposite side.\r\n\r\nAmong other things, if we got Engulfing Flames in the center of the room at the same time as the seeds, it was pretty much a wipe since the ranged and tanks were divided and unable to stack for healing and damage reduction - especially if we were using the circle strategy.  EF was particularly annoying for the 2nd seed when the room would get divided by flames, followed by seed, followed by the hammer wave.  No matter which configuration we used it ended badly.  Are you just screwed if you have seeds and a center EF at the same time?\r\n\r\nGoing back to formations, using the center worked decently until EF divided the room and no one could stack anymore.  So we tried stacking the raid on a side and then moving to the other as we got seeds.  This seemed like a messier approach since people were scattered in terms of how far they had crossed the room by the time the seeds went off, so that heals and damage reductions weren't getting everyone.  Is there a minimum damage dealt by the seeds so that there's a distance we should have been stopping at sooner?  We also still had a difficulties with the EF again, and getting everyone to the front on the 2nd seed to avoid the hammer.\r\n\r\nAny suggestions on formations and how to deal with EF/seed at the same time would be *greatly* appreciated!  We're hoping for a kill in the next night or two, but I'm still afraid to see the chasing meteors.", "date": "2011-07-12T18:28:17-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Keep your raid spread out using the circle tactic. The timing is tight but even if EF decides to take the middle of the room with seeds out you will still have a few precious seconds between EF fading and the seeds detonating, people need to be ready to run to the middle.  Also - On the second seed wave if you're stacking in one spot Ragnaros will ALWAYS do a Sulfuras Smash just after the seeds detonate, when he casts this just move forward so you're stood next to the edge of the lava pool he's in. It's not pleasent when he squashes the raid.", "creationdate": "2011-07-16T22:39:35-05:00", "id": 252845, "rating": 11, "commentid": 1468274, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rygol", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 1468744, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "526684", "body": "Anyone know if ragnaros can parry? Usually bosses that are like him cant parry, but idk because you can actually attack him from behind if you turn him one way and the melee attack the other way.", "date": "2011-07-13T09:27:05-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, he can parry. This doesn't matter very much for phase 1 or 2 since his transitions are percentage based, and in phase 1 you don't want to spread your melee out too far from your tanks on 10 man otherwise healers may have difficulty reaching them. In phase 3, I would strongly advise trying to keep your melee far on the opposite side to the tank to avoid parries for the very much needed DPS in this phase (Without going too far into the corner to avoid being trapped by meteors). Although that might give healing range a problem, provided people move out of bad stuff there is no raid damage in", "creationdate": "2011-07-13T09:27:06-05:00", "id": 488208, "rating": 15, "commentid": 1468744, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "534473", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 1469469, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Grandine", "body": "I wonder if we could have just bribed the (now) neutral Neptulon and Therazane to kill Ragnaros for us...we did scratch their backs...", "date": "2011-07-14T03:28:57-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Neptulon gets abducted by Ozumat at the end of the Throne of the Tides encounter. I didn't notice it until I read about it, really. As to Therazane, well... Who knows, she doesn't really like us that much. And it's strongly implied Ragnaros is the second most powerful of the four behind Neptulon himself.", "creationdate": "2011-07-20T10:40:27-05:00", "id": 253588, "rating": 11, "commentid": 1469469, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karoxen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 1473554, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "darknesscalls", "body": "We don't have a huge amount of information on heroic yet, but there is another phase that starts at 10%.\r\n\r\nAt this point, Ragnaros rises from his lava pool and walks around, while Cenarius, Arch Druid Hamuul Runetotem, and Malfurion Stormrage come to aid you. Some RP occurs and Ragnaros heals to 50% health. Apparently there is some reason why he heals only to 50% and not 100% of his health, without knowing the RP yet we won't know for certain, but I'm sure the info will be released by a guild sooner or later.", "date": "2011-07-18T17:41:01-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Perhaps he cannot regenerate to 100% because we interrupted something he was doing? Awakened him earlier than expected? perhaps, \"Too Soon\"?", "creationdate": "2011-07-19T09:15:05-05:00", "id": 488564, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1473554, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Gibsonboi1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He goes to 50% so that he drops back to 25% earlier, which means another execution phase.", "creationdate": "2011-07-29T05:30:37-05:00", "id": 255342, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1473554, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rekijan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
