{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1922953, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Stabhorn", "body": "Ragnaros lies supine, the extinguished remnants of Sulfuron lay beside him. He starts as the ghost of Fandral Staghelm materializes over him, and the fires fade from his eyes. As Fandral kneels next to him, Ragnaros places a hand on his Majordomo's chest.\n    Ragnaros: Fandral! Is it... over?\n    Fandral lays a comforting hand on Ragnaros' gauntlet.\n    Fandral: At long last. No Lord rules forever, my Master.\n   Ragnaros: I see... only darkness... before... me...\n    Ragnaros' eyes roll back into his head and he dies, his hand falling to the ground. Fandral closes his Master's eyes and gently lays him on the ground as Malfurion walks in.\n    Fandral: Without its Master's command, the restless Fire Elementals will become an even greater threat to this world.\n    Fandral stands, facing Malfurion.\n    Fandral: Control must be maintained. There must always be... a Fire Lord.\n    Fandral's ghost disappears. Malfurion walks over to Sulfurus, bends down to pick it up and examines the front of it.\n    Malfurion: The weight of such a burden...it must be mine, for there is no other to--\n    Hamuul: Malfurion...\n    The scorched caricature of Hamuul is revealed, sitting atop the Fire Lord's throne.\n    Hamuul: You hold a grim destiny in your hands, Stormrage...but it is not your own.\n    Malfurion: Runetotem! By the dream...\n    Hamuul: Leyara's flame...sealed my fate...The world of the living can no longer comfort me.\n    Malfurion  has ascended the stairs to the Throne and we see him taking the last two steps to stand before Hamuul.\n    Hamuul: Place the hammer in my hands, Malfurion. Forevermore, I will be the jailor of the burning.\n    Malfurion: No, old friend. I cannot...\n    Hamuul: DO IT MALFURION! You and these brave heroes have your own destinies to fulfill. This last act of service... is mine.\n    Malfurion turns toward Hamuul with the Hammer of Ragnaros cradled in his hands before him.\n    Malfurion: You will not be forgotten, thero'shan.\n    Hamuul: I MUST be forgotten, Malfurion! If the world is to live free from the tyranny of fear - they must never know what was done here today.\n    Malfurion nods and accedes to Hamuul's request, sliding the hammer into his hands. The chamber begins to shake violently as Malfurion looks around. There is a flash of light and Hamuul's eyes are glowing golden yellow as Sulfurus reignites.\n    Hamuul: Tell them only that that Ragnaros is dead...\n    Hamuul: ... and that Cenarius died with him.\n    The Throne bursts into flame, consuming Hamuul in an inferno.\n    Hamuul: NOW GO. LEAVE THIS PLACE - AND NEVER RETURN.", "date": "2013-12-02T13:15:40-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "But Runetotem is the one that got burned, wouldn't that make more sense?", "creationdate": "2015-09-27T05:12:39-05:00", "id": 901382, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1922953, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "gojtron", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-05-14T17:16:31-05:00", 1, "Stabhorn"]}
