{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 2066380, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "shadosan", "body": "Went at him as a lvl 100 shaman enhancement, ilvl 638.\n\n[b][i]25man heroic :[/i][/b]\n\nNothing dangerous really happen, stay out of fire. You don't have to care about the adds that run to the hammer when he submerge.\n\nWhen he is almost dead, he will return with 10m hp (and legs!) and the pool of lava he was in will cool down, allowing you to walk on it. Reserve some or all of your CDs for that part, since it may hurt badly.", "date": "2014-12-11T14:35:44-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-12-11T14:47:45-06:00", 1, "shadosan"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 2070740, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lawngnomes", "body": "Super easy to solo as a 638 WW Monk on 25H, just dps'd through his non-walking part, avoiding the traps and avoiding his other abilities - the  Sons of Flame don't matter.\n\nOnce he got his legs, I just kept dps'ing, then hopped in the green buff once I got in trouble, then hopped in the blue buff when green expired, and it was smooth sailing from there.", "date": "2014-12-16T23:42:23-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-12-16T23:42:54-06:00", 2, "Lawngnomes"]}
