{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 209181, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "68112", "body": "Good'ol Ragnaros, takes me way back to the \"Loot the damn dog\" and the \"lol somone pulled Golemag\" days. My Favorite Boss along with Nefarian in BWL. :D\r\n\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSpecialAttack01.wav\")\r\nPaste in Chat for some \"oldschoolraider nostalgia\" :)", "date": "2007-12-29T06:22:54-06:00", "rating": 60, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "just wanted to add its the full   /script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSpecialAttack01.wav\")  and that 2 and 3 yield:   2: taste the flames of sulfuron  3: my patience is dwindling, come gnats, to your death", "creationdate": "2008-02-24T08:20:26-06:00", "id": 26649, "rating": 30, "commentid": 209181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "2OfDiamonds", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "no, you can't.", "creationdate": "2009-01-10T15:45:05-06:00", "id": 379382, "rating": -1, "commentid": 209181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dimish", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks for the macros :) They're win!", "creationdate": "2009-08-11T23:38:50-05:00", "id": 419979, "rating": 0, "commentid": 209181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "keroblade", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 231499, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "34511", "body": "Ragnaros is the first true epic fight old players had to deal with. While going throught the whole Molten Core dungeon was challenging for many of us and is piece of cake now... Ragnaros still has this little something that makes him different.\n\nWe were young and naive, and this fight truely felt epic as we had to have 40 players playing 110% to kill him. The pride of downing him for the first time is something you keep in mind for a long time !\n\nI don't feel like burning crusade could match this fight (as well as several others from the old word). Most likely because we have grown and don't look at the game the same way, but also because now we are running 25 mans raids.\n\nEasier to play, but less fun in the end I think.\n\nAnyway if you have never been in Molten Core, gather up 10-15 people and go ahead ;) You will be surprised that you can still wipe there despite the instance being tuned for level 60 blue geared players ;)", "date": "2008-02-08T04:24:32-06:00", "rating": 113, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Whilst Archi, Illidan and Kil'jaeden didn't phase me too much (I was still elated to have killed them), I have to say that Kael, and to a lesser extent Vashj, are the two fights that have held the greatest pride factor for me - much moreso than Rag. Yes, we'd seen it all before, but Vashj and Kael were giant roadblocks made of titanium that had to be destroyed in order to proceed further (prior to 2.4 of course). And they weren't easy fights - you had to [b]EARN[/b] your attunement to MH/BT.  When we finally got Vashj down after a few nights of attempts, vent erupted in fervor. We were half wa", "creationdate": "2008-02-08T04:24:33-06:00", "id": 359824, "rating": 1, "commentid": 231499, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jaxsonbateman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I still get the chills remembering the first time my guild down Rag... Still have the killshot of it :-)", "creationdate": "2008-10-20T19:06:57-05:00", "id": 51737, "rating": 20, "commentid": 231499, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Siralex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]When we finally got Vashj down after a few nights of attempts,[/quote]  While I don't wish to take anything away from your accomplishemnts, your few days attempting Vashj are nothing compared to the months some guilds spent trying to down Rag.", "creationdate": "2009-03-02T19:31:18-06:00", "id": 83393, "rating": 34, "commentid": 231499, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cheesechamp", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I cackled in this raid. Myself (Protection warrior), a shadow priest, and her ret pally husband went in to get old school patterns. Instead we 3-manned the entire raid and laughed at how easy Raggy is these days. As I joked after, when he first came out, beating him was like slaying the devil. Now, it's like beating up a toddler.", "creationdate": "2010-09-24T21:33:41-05:00", "id": 459147, "rating": 1, "commentid": 231499, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TheLustful", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yea I remember spending probably 3 months working our way to rag and finally killing him. But oh man were they fun times!", "creationdate": "2011-02-22T14:00:34-06:00", "id": 227441, "rating": 1, "commentid": 231499, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "786595", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-03-17T17:08:36-05:00", 1, "34511"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 279202, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "74389", "body": "10 of us went Rag last week and we downed him in 1 minute and 45 secs. So he didnt Submerge or anything.", "date": "2008-04-29T10:46:54-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 292821, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "yoshimo", "body": "I need some clarification on the wrath-spell.\r\nWhose aggro is reduced by which amount if he casts this?\r\nthe whole raid , melees only?  threat halfed or complete whipe? google isnt helpful at this one----", "date": "2008-05-22T17:19:18-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The Wrath spell is a melee oriented knockback. Think Murmur's explosion if you have done Shadow Labs. Melee at the time would attack until the knockback warning. They'd move to the edge near the lava and they would/should be safe from the knockbacks effects. The knockback sends melee out and up. Therefore, landing on land sometimes wasn't the case with many melee dying in lava.", "creationdate": "2008-05-27T12:09:30-05:00", "id": 34766, "rating": 5, "commentid": 292821, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "144370", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
