{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 677266, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "279763", "body": "I also managed to solo Ragnaros, and all previous 9 bosses before him, as a protection paladin. My main spec is retribution, so I only had decent tanking gear and around 289FR with my aura.\r\nArtharas' post above me was very helpful, especially about the \"sweet spot\" you must stand on so that when he pushes you back you'll land unharmed in the lava.\r\n\r\nFight lasted 50minutes. I didn't try at all to avoid his knockback, instead I threw a flare on the \"sweetspot\" Artharas said and immediately after Ragnaros knocked me back, I swam to the flare, Holy light, and fight again :)\r\nThe adds phase was simply a chance for me to regain a full mana bar, no problems at all with them.\r\nI used wisdom both on seal and judgement.\r\n\r\nOnly 2 interesting points I can add to the previous posts:\r\n1.Two or three times during the fight, after been thrown into the lava, somehow I managed to have less than 10k health. If that happens, bubble or LoH immediately, the danger of wipe is imminent :)\r\n2.My tanking sword broke at around 80% because of the previous engagement I had with Majordomo. When my healing mace which I equipped next, turned yellow at 30%, I deployed a repair bot (didn't know if that would work but it did!), repaired to the full, and in 2 seconds I was ready as new :) So you engineers out there, no need to even bring a 2nd weapon. When it breaks, just repair on-site :)\r\n\r\nAgathoklis, human Retribution paladin, Bloodhoof", "date": "2009-04-15T08:09:23-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
