{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 821578, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Liquids", "body": "Soloable as a lvl 80 prot paladin. \r\n\r\nThe fight is not very hard, but it is unfortuantely very RNG. \r\nThe only dangerous thing is taking falling damage from the knockback. With correct positioning you should land in the lava every time and avoid the damage, but if your position is just a little bit off or you are unlucky you can get falling damage and possibly die. \r\nWhen you get knocked back, look to see if it looks like you will get falling damage and have your finger ready on bubble/LoH. Remember that Ardent Defender wont prevent you from dying to falling damage. \r\nAlso note that you will never actually land on ground, but the edge of the lava pool is shallow enough for you to take falling damage. \r\n\r\nYou should position such that you are facing roughly west and thus will be knocked back to the east. Get a feeling for how you need to face to be knocked in the best possible direction, and make sure always to return to that position ASAP. \r\n\r\nI used these buffs primarily: Fire aura, RF, BoSanc, seal of corruption. I used JoL the entire fight. Sacred shield is good to keep up, a good time to cast it is when you are knocked back or swimming back. \r\nYou can switch to SoL if you get low on health, but remember to switch back at some point; the more dps you do, the less time there is for getting an unlucky knockback. \r\nI did not wear any FR gear. \r\n\r\n\r\nSons of Ragnaros is your chance to get full health and mana. When 8 of them are hitting you, BoSanc will get you to full mana quickly. Finish all but 2-3 sons, heal to full with HL and then stop dps while divine plea + BoSanc gets you to full mana. I only melee'd once every 10 sec to keep DP going. \r\nWhen you are full on mana again, finish the sons off and return to your position for knock back immediately.", "date": "2009-08-24T15:20:56-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 821925, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "257289", "body": "Solo'd as a feral druid. If you feral charge him when he throws you up in the air, it makes the fight pretty easy. Save berserk for the adds, make sure you barkskin/hot before they come, they do a good bit of damage.", "date": "2009-08-25T00:17:47-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
