{"commentv2": 1, "number": 76, "id": 832329, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "164838", "body": "Easily soloable as a Ret Paladin wearing Illidan glaive tanking FR gear. I believe I had ~440FR with aura, and it was basically tank and spank swapping between seal of Light and Wisdom. Only real danger is if you cop a punt and don't land on soft ground, in which case you may need to stop and heal yourself back up.\r\nCompared to what you've had to do to get here it's a simple, yet drawn out fight.", "date": "2009-09-05T05:30:17-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 77, "id": 834839, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "258919", "body": "This guy is pulling a Kael'Thas on us.\r\n\r\nIn the upcoming Cataclysm expansion (to be released in 2010), he returns from banishment to attempt to burn down Nordrassil, the World Tree, in Hyjal. The tree will be protected by the newly returned Malfurion Stormrage and his Cenarius army.\r\n\r\nWhat this will mean for Molten Core is not certain, but it is likely this instance will stay as it is (much like Stratholme still exists despite Rivendare's return in Northrend)", "date": "2009-09-07T21:05:57-05:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "not really, ragnaros wasn't killed he was simply banished (we loot only his hammer for that reason, just as we loot only kil'jaeden's medallion rather than him)  because of that he can return if the proper conditions are met, Nefarian on the other hand was killed, and beheaded so how does he gets' back on cataclysm is simply the \"kael'tas effect\"  that being said, most (if not all) classic instances will be removed, or reworked.  by removed means the portal is removed, and the inside becomes a part of the regular map (this is what happens to nefarian's lair, we enter new isntances from his thr", "creationdate": "2009-09-07T21:05:58-05:00", "id": 429631, "rating": -2, "commentid": 834839, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 264, "username": "Rankkor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That was ridiculously wrong. They aren't removing any instances. Bornakk, a blue poster, responded to a post much like yours by saying that this idea was mistaken. He said they will tell us if anything is being removed from the game, and there has been absolutely no mention of any instances being removed.", "creationdate": "2009-11-07T22:14:34-06:00", "id": 430668, "rating": 7, "commentid": 834839, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "164509", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
