{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 865022, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "178348", "body": "I was able to solo him as a ret pally using only the fire resist aura in pve gear.  I have a few emblem of conquest pieces and 4/5 tier 7 (10 man Naxx).\r\n\r\nStrat:\r\nUse seal of light, judge light, always keep up sacred shield.  Instant flash of light yourself when you can to keep the HoTs up.  Position yourself so you're knocked back into the lava when you fall, otherwise I don't believe this fight is possible.  When Rag submerges, stun an add and use hand of salvation (if you have the glyph).  Keep 1 add alive and use divine plea if necessary.\r\n\r\nYou'll only need to bring one weapon with you as ret as long as it's repaired before starting.\r\n\r\nI frapsed the fight.  Not sure exactly how long it took, but the total file size of 2 files was ~7 gigs... Probably around 15 minutes.  If I get a chance, I'll post it.", "date": "2009-10-12T12:10:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 872767, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "467494", "body": "Soloable by prot pally and feral druid. On seperate visits, of course.\r\n\r\nProt:\r\n\r\nThere's a rock opposite of where Majordomo summons Rag. When you get knocked back, make sure to land on that thing. Fire resist aura very handy, no other fire resist really necessary. Rotate cooldowns - first knockback, use bubble before landing. Third/fourth, use protection to mitigate his Wrath of Ragnaros attacks. When you make your way back from the rock, jump into the lava rather than the ground - the fall damage is unpleasant. Other than that, Rag isn't a very hard hitter. Swap to a healing weapon if you need healing, get yourself up, get back on him. I'll say one thing though, the fight's long, and Rag melts your weapon. On my druid, I ended up killing him with my fishing pole, and on my pally, I went through my melee weapon and half my healing weapon.\r\n\r\nFeral:\r\n\r\nStand as far as you can from him, but still in melee range. If he knocks you back, feral charge back quickly. If you're too close, it will consume the charge, but not let you come back, and then you have to face his annoying fire blasts. If you're not comfortable with that, use the safety rock on the side opposite of where Domo used to be as a back up. If you're feral charging correctly, you don't need any fire resist at all. If you're uncomfortable with feral charges for whatever reason, 200 or more fire resist trivializes the fire blasts.", "date": "2009-10-22T05:55:11-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 1, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I attempted this on my paladin not too long ago, yeah, insta-FoL does eliminate the need for block and other mitigation.  However, I found that as ret, I took too much damage from his Wrath attacks. I could heal back to full when I was in melee, sometimes swapping to SoL, however after quite a few attempts, I kept slipping up around 50-75% health, where I would receive a few too many hits from not being in melee, and then slowly dying trying to get back.  It's completely possible to do as a ret paladin, but some fire resist (something over the 130 I had), extra stamina, or additional buffs may", "creationdate": "2009-10-22T05:55:12-05:00", "id": 438171, "rating": 1, "commentid": 872767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "467494", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For whatever reason, my last comment was purged.  The condensed version stated that Ragnaros is soloable by a ret pally.  So for all you ret pallies out there, it's more than possible.", "creationdate": "2009-11-04T16:00:22-06:00", "id": 130724, "rating": 11, "commentid": 872767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "178348", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Funny enough, I was going to try it on my pally as ret. I'm able to do him on my druid using almost only cat form (bear form for feral charge), but I didn't consider using the pally because you don't get to charge back.  Large increase in difficulty, or do the insta-FoL trivialize the fight?", "creationdate": "2009-11-14T05:05:01-06:00", "id": 132368, "rating": 1, "commentid": 872767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "467494", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "They certainly trivialize a lot of other encounters. I imagine SoV/SoM would be better for this fight, as the DoT will sustain your DPS whilst you're out of melee range due to the knockbacks. I may attempt it when my ret gear is good enough.  And I'll make sure not to sell my Edge of Ruin when I upgrade it. The breaking weapons problem hadn't even occurred to me.", "creationdate": "2009-11-15T07:02:18-06:00", "id": 132578, "rating": 1, "commentid": 872767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "boiledelephant", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Great call on the feral charge for bears. To clarify for people who don't understand - he means you feral charge -while you are in midair during the knockback- This allows you to avoid all knockback damage and get you right to the fight. Start mashing your feral charge the second you hear \"Taste the flames of Sulfuron!\".  I didn't even have to heal using this method and ended the fight at 100% health.  Great tip - Thanks!", "creationdate": "2010-04-15T01:27:15-05:00", "id": 159021, "rating": 2, "commentid": 872767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nemspyda", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 81, "id": 896270, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "294737", "body": "[quote]A creature who waged war against the titans when the world was young. A monster of unimaginable power. A power that dwarfs Kil'Jaedan or Illidan.[/quote]\r\n\r\nA creature that got mauled to death by a feral druid. 11 minute fight. Feral Charge heavily mitigates the fall damage, but doesn't eliminate it. Buffed with 50 resist flask, 40 hit/sta food to reach the old world 9% cap, 132 stamina scroll, mark of the wild, and drums of forgotten kings. The only time I needed to hit a cooldown was when I opted to hit my screenshot button in midair once, rather than feral charge (slight delay as the file writes, and only a split second window of opportunity on the charge). I did hit berserk when the sons came out, so I could time the next wave. To my knowledge, this is the first solo with screenshots to back it up. Anyone attempting to wear him down through high mitigation should bring a backup weapon, your weapon will [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=21388]take damage[/url] as you fight him. The only boss along the way that wasn't soloable was Golemagg. It takes some high DPS to beat his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=13880]stacks[/url], pally could probably manage it with bubble though. Enjoy and GL farming!\r\n\r\n[url=http://i440.photobucket.com/albums/qq121/mmiles01/WoWScrnShot_112109_012354.jpg]Minions, yum[/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://i440.photobucket.com/albums/qq121/mmiles01/WoWScrnShot_112109_012441.jpg]Go, trusty Bearachute![/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://i440.photobucket.com/albums/qq121/mmiles01/WoWScrnShot_112109_014335.jpg]With 4 Durability Left[/url]\r\n\r\nIf you attempt to kill him too, beware: He is red, and slightly larger than your average monster of unimaginable power.", "date": "2009-11-21T01:14:33-06:00", "rating": 68, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This was only a fraction of his strength mind you, a strength you can see in Firelands.", "creationdate": "2012-05-21T17:43:41-05:00", "id": 545070, "rating": 7, "commentid": 896270, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bronius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-11-21T01:29:32-06:00", 5, "294737"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 897796, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PilsnerDk", "body": "Solo'd him in just 12 minutes as a ret paladin in full dps gear, with ret aura, BoM and SoV. My gear is mostly ilvl 219-226 epics.\r\n\r\nIt wasn't very hard at all. A good place to stand is a spot where you land on an oddly-shapen cliff when you get blasted. I forgot the geographical orientation of it, but you'll notice it. This greatly reduces the falling damage you take when you get blasted. The Magma Blast typically hits for 3k with fire resistance aura, and is only cast every 3 seconds or so, so it's not a big threat.\r\n\r\nThe biggest threat was really the sons, they hit rather hard and there are 8 of them. Had to use LoH once on them.\r\n\r\nI had repair bots ready, but I didn't need them at all, ended with my weapon at 63/120 durability. :)", "date": "2009-11-22T11:47:59-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 83, "id": 913568, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "490052", "body": "Soloed it as a lvl 80 affliction warlock.\n\nFirst phase is a breeze, just nuked my heart out.\n\nSecond phase is truly a difficult part. Eight adds come out and they hit really hard, especially if you're a clothie like me.\nI used howl of terror, fear, banish, healthstone, death coil and a healing potion, and it was still a close call.\n\nKilled him before he could slap me with another add phase.\n\nUninteresting drops, but now I'm 10/10 Molten Core solo. It was a challenge and extremely fun. =)\n\n\nDeionarra, horde warlock of Vek'nilash EU.", "date": "2009-12-11T09:35:01-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Utterly destroyed him as an Affliction PvP warlock. Just have your felhunter tank the boss. I was wearing 1 piece of fire resist {which, in hindsight, was unnecessary}, however I did use Runescroll of Fortitude, Drums of Kings and Drums of the Wild {also unnecessary}. I have no clue why you were worried about phase 2, when the mobs come out, just put up Corruption and CoA and then /sleep while they die in a few seconds. I was never in any danger of dropping below 50%.  Other than that, keep DoTs up on the boss, health funnel your pet, spam shadow bolt or drain life when your pet has plenty of ", "creationdate": "2009-12-11T09:35:02-06:00", "id": 449861, "rating": 1, "commentid": 913568, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fingulfin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-12-11T09:36:45-06:00", 2, "490052"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 84, "id": 926550, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "FlayOnDarkIron", "body": "Brought to you by Tarren Mill... Ragnar-Os!\r\nThe only cereal with the Molten Core!\r\nBY FIBER BE PURGED!\r\nTASTE THE FLAVORS OF SULFURON!\r\nTWO SCOOPS, EXECUTUS! TWO SCOOPS!", "date": "2009-12-23T08:51:57-06:00", "rating": 382, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[url=http://wow.joystiq.com/2007/08/01/breakfast-topic-best-voiceacting/]Credit where credits due![/url]  Edit: the article preceded this comment by 2 years. While the article doesn't claim to be original (in fact, the comments probably preceded the first Ragnaros kills), I couldn't find an earlier source. It's a bit rough to leave the comment up baldly when it had been in circulation for at least 2 years.", "creationdate": "2011-09-22T20:39:57-05:00", "id": 491866, "rating": 7, "commentid": 926550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "gamerunknown", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=5855!", "creationdate": "2012-02-21T12:35:37-06:00", "id": 521425, "rating": 21, "commentid": 926550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "838725", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I will make this worth 100 vote ups. You deserve it.", "creationdate": "2012-06-27T17:18:02-05:00", "id": 552790, "rating": 2, "commentid": 926550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Skornaq", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This boss is now easily soloable at max level.", "creationdate": "2013-01-03T11:51:58-06:00", "id": 618786, "rating": -5, "commentid": 926550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "438040", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I 2 manned him with a 60 twink frost mage and my friend's 60 twink blood death knight.", "creationdate": "2013-06-19T12:49:54-05:00", "id": 670419, "rating": -4, "commentid": 926550, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "westonjust", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
