{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 931783, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "509845", "body": "Is he soloable by a prot warrior?", "date": "2009-12-29T14:42:34-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just soloed him as a Prot/Fury Warrior!  0/31/40, glyphed for Bloodthirst and Enraged Regeneration.  I was wearing mostly my normal prot gear, but I also had the 4 pieces of fire resist gear you can buy with Badges of Justice and The Fel Barrier from heroic Mana Tombs. Drums of the Wild and a Lesser Flask of Resistance brought my Fire Resistance to 326.  I made sure to stand where I'd get knocked into the lava, then I'd pop my intercept macro to expedite the return trip. I also kept Improved Demo Shout and Thunderclap up at all times.  Until tonight I could easily solo everything but Gehennas.", "creationdate": "2009-12-29T14:42:35-06:00", "id": 452372, "rating": 2, "commentid": 931783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "618266", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Probably not.  I took a prot/arms friend of mine along with my pally. Since I can solo him, I went ret, but since he couldn't take hits, he went prot.  Judgement of light helped him tremendously, and with Sacred Shield on him he was healing more than he was taking. But no, he wouldn't have done it if my pally wasn't there.  However, I have no idea if the Warr solo spec can take down rag...", "creationdate": "2010-01-11T17:59:42-06:00", "id": 142796, "rating": 1, "commentid": 931783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "467494", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "i can CONFIRm he is as of cataclysm, almost solo'd him today, no buffs but my own and got him down to less than 200k health, i have mostly level 81-83 greens so a geared 85 could definately do this", "creationdate": "2010-12-20T03:07:43-06:00", "id": 468956, "rating": 0, "commentid": 931783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "735077", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 87, "id": 945003, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "467494", "body": "[quote]...To my knowledge, this is the first solo with screenshots to back it up...[/quote]\n\n[url=http://img27.imageshack.us/img27/3940/ragkill.jpg]Orly?[/url]\n\n[url=http://img695.imageshack.us/img695/7500/onfire.jpg]NO WAI[/url]\n\n[url=http://img137.imageshack.us/img137/6929/golemagg2.jpg]<insert silly reference>[/url] <-- Golemagg is totally soloable, and I wish you luck on'm!\n\n(And yes, my weapon broke... I finished him with my fishing pole equipped)", "date": "2010-01-11T18:07:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-01-11T18:07:48-06:00", 1, "467494"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 88, "id": 949249, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chasecanales", "body": "Hes coming back! He will be a boss in the new expansion, Cataclysm, and hes mad and out for revenge. He is one of the 4 element bosses.", "date": "2010-01-16T21:48:27-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Molten Core was merely a setback?", "creationdate": "2010-01-16T23:26:25-06:00", "id": 143696, "rating": 33, "commentid": 949249, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sorsa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 89, "id": 951962, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "chaosbringer127", "body": "2manned Ragnaros as a resto shaman in ~t8 gear and a destro warlock in ~t7.5 gear.\r\n\r\nBasically this fight is about positioning, let the voidwalker tank, and you and the lock have to stand in the middle edge of the circle so when he does the knockback you dont get out of range of the void. Drop fire resist, it helps alot. Whenever he summons his adds just let your DPS blow them up, rinse and repeat. Probably solable as a protection paladin.", "date": "2010-01-19T23:17:57-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 90, "id": 959141, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "sugaki", "body": "Soloed as DK Blood DPS in my DPS gear and fire res gear. Once you have enough fire resistance it's pretty easy, so long as you have the spot down to fight him. Took me a wipe to figure the right spot so I won't get blown back into hard ground.\r\n\r\nI don't recommend doing this without any fire res gear, as his fire attack does 6000 damage. I put on 330 fire res and his damage was very tiny and manageable. The sons adds did trivial damage as well. Once you get enough fire res, the main concern is positioning yourself so you fall in the right spot.", "date": "2010-01-28T16:48:14-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes try and position yourself with you back towards the biggest lava pool if soloing. This will make fall damage non-existant. The only thing you do have to deal with is the lava damage and his ranged attack that does about 6000. Otherwise just keep your health up and you should be fine.", "creationdate": "2011-12-08T18:02:02-06:00", "id": 285270, "rating": 0, "commentid": 959141, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Russiankid001", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 961992, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kkongo", "body": "I wonder what he'll yell if you encounter him in Mount Hyjal at Cataclysm?\r\n\r\n[i]\"Molten Core was merely a setback!\"[/i]", "date": "2010-02-01T05:23:38-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 968092, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "541144", "body": "Two manned Molten Core. \r\n\r\nAchronos - Asassination Rogue\r\n\r\nHighrise - Holy Paladin\r\n\r\nPretty simple, except for the boss with the ton of healers. Had to get each one out of line of sight one by one and dps down.", "date": "2010-02-06T21:27:33-06:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 988986, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "LoreAddict", "body": "Step 1: Wait for him to submerge and spawn the sons.\n\nStep 2: Get a warlock to banish one of them, kill the rest.\n\nStep 3: Make a shaman kill Ragnaros by himself.\n\nSo you have the [i]banished[/i] son of the [i]Firelord[/i], right besides the [i]master of all four elements[/i] as he defeats him.\n\nNot exactly canon, but close enough.\n\nNow if we only had a comet...", "date": "2010-03-02T12:41:18-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Get this  http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21891", "creationdate": "2010-03-02T18:43:50-06:00", "id": 443778, "rating": 0, "commentid": 988986, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Corbon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-05-18T13:38:15-05:00", 3, "LoreAddict"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 997731, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1517", "body": "Confirmed. I solo'd Ragnaros on my (4400gs?) prot paladin with no fire resist other than aura. Was still easy. There were a few close calls and it took 25 minutes, but wasn't a real problem. Weapon broke when Rag was at ~10%, and I was forced to switch to my healing weapon.\r\n\r\nInterestingly enough, the Sons of Flame were the easiest part. They allowed me to bring my mana and HP back up to full.\r\n\r\nBasically I judged light and used seal of light/wisdom as needed to keep either up. If you stand where the ranged DPS used to stand in classic (at least, in the guilds I ran it with) you will get launched back into the lava. I took falling damage twice out of countless knockbacks.", "date": "2010-03-15T00:55:19-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 1001007, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaiservash", "body": "Soloed as DK Blood Tank, and a Moonkin (to make it quicker). I died once, from falling DMG, i didn't landed in the lava, CRsed me and np from that point. A DK Tank can solo almost all bosses, except gehennas (curse nulls lethal strike healing), and some help is welcome in Magmadar, if u aggro the dogs in a fear... get ready to be deleted, but u can take a mage, moonkin or whatever who does AoE's, down the dogs and ask him/her to let u kill it by yourself.\n\nHave fun trying and excuse my english, not mi \"lengua materna\" :)", "date": "2010-03-19T22:32:22-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-03-19T22:33:11-05:00", 1, "Kaiservash"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1001580, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sylene", "body": "If you clear the instance till Ragnaros, and you leave it there, the boss will be there for 2 hours, then it will despawn. If you want to kill it later, you have to kill Majordomo again. [b]Majordomo repops every 12 hours.[/b] He wont drop loots again if you killed it for second time. \r\nGood luck", "date": "2010-03-20T18:16:42-05:00", "rating": 61, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1032866, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "583553", "body": "how much gold this guy drops in solo anywayz?", "date": "2010-05-04T23:16:55-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "100 or something; soloed him as a retri, so it was pretty easy :)", "creationdate": "2010-06-03T16:57:47-05:00", "id": 451339, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1032866, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "610788", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1041816, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "95531", "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nAs a person that never got the chance to fight Ragnaros in Vanilla (I was in a non raiding social guild) I would like to know for soloing purposes does Ragnaros melee swings deal physical or fire damage?\r\n\r\nFrom what i remember Baron Geddon melee swings are all fire damage so I'm wondering if its the case with Ragnaros also? This would basicly mean that Fire Res would be good to mitigate dmg done to you.\r\n\r\nAlso another thing,\r\n\r\nWhen he does a knockback is there a safespot for a person where you wouldnt get knocked back? What i mean is, is there a spot where lets say a healer could stand (At healing range) and during the knockback \"fly\" against a \"wall\" hes against and this way avoid having to run back to original position?\r\n\r\nIm considering bringing a healer on my other computer as my main class cant heal and I imagine the knockback would be the most annoying thing to handle in this fight if youre trying to control 2 characters yourself. Having a healer at a kind of safe spot would basicly mean i could concentrate moving to melee range with my main only and this way avoid the extra dmg that he does when noones in melee range.\r\n\r\nAnyone able to clarify these points?", "date": "2010-05-19T07:22:14-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Now that my Druid is geared up in decent Resto gear I went to MC last night and did the whole place.  I have 2 accounts and logged into them on separate computers.  I have a Warrior on the other one and Druid on the other one.  Every boss was pretty easy considering I could use 2 characters. Only problem is the fact that I have to use 2 computers to control 2 characters. For the druid I made a separate higher scale action bar which i filled with target+cast macros of the main spells I would need. This made it somewhat bearable.  Only troublesome parts were Geddon and Ragnaros and some other bo", "creationdate": "2010-05-19T07:22:15-05:00", "id": 450284, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1041816, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "95531", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ragnaros just solo'ed as a Retridin, about 25.4K hp unbuffed. Seal of Light + Judgement of Wisdom, T10 2 piece bonus was very helpful to keep health up. Biggest problem is the knockback, stand where the closest -big- patch of lava is so you fall in it. Keep Sacred Shield up as much as possible to negate damage and just Divine Storm through the adds. Took about five or six minutes.  All bosses solo'ed, but mostly in Prot specc. Retri used on Ragnaros for more hits due to Melt Weapon and higher durability.", "creationdate": "2010-06-10T16:08:48-05:00", "id": 451842, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1041816, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "614728", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "SoL isn't necessary as retpal, I used Seal of corruption with ICC gear (251/264) and the libram of valiance. The Bryntoll axe helps a lot.", "creationdate": "2010-08-04T07:58:24-05:00", "id": 456206, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1041816, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "idrith", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1066889, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bitehattori", "body": "I think this verse fits Ol' Raggy, from the MEGA MAN 2 by The Adventures Of Duane And BrandO song - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QUEO9Mfmn4M\nWords were changed, original words are in brackets.\n\n\n[quote]Raid:\n\u2018Sup Heat Man let\u2019s do this fast.\nMy pussy-ass brother just bailed on your ass.\nIt\u2019s time to blow bubbles, the bad kind though.[/quote]\n[quote]Raggy:\nDon\u2019t get too close, I might blow.\nWho knows what flows from the Earth? I DO!\nI\u2019m gonna spew red goo all over your shoes.\nI got a face for radio and a box for a suit.\nRaid: Blizzard (Was Capcom) really didn\u2019t spend much time on you.\nRaggy: NOPE.\nRaid: Check it out, I\u2019m tired of you.\nRaid: I got my raid(Cannon) ready, I got Grindin\u2019(Huntin') to do.[/quote]\n[quote]Raggy: I\u2019ve got more hot than a cow has moo.\nI will burn you with my flame!\nZippo is my middle name!\nI\u2019m done $%^&in\u2019 around, eight-bit clown.[/quote]\n[quote]Raid: Here\u2019s a bubble have fun six feet underground- DEAD.[/quote]", "date": "2010-06-26T21:31:01-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-06-26T21:32:06-05:00", 1, "bitehattori"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1071557, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ludafrank", "body": "Solo'd with my prot pally with mostly 10 ICC and some 264 frost emblem bought gear and a [b]BOA WEAPON,[/b] that parts very important. The fight lasted 20 mins according to the time left on BoS. Using SoCor most of the fight and only switching judgements for hp/mana unless under 50% hp while fighting Rag then I'd switch seals. Making sure to land in the lava every knockback it was really a piece of cake with the 264 libram proc'ing on SoR and keeping Holy Shield up almost all the time using the normal 69696 tank rotation. I took next to 0 damage while in melee range and the elemental fire debuff was mostly absorbed by Sacred Shield then on knockbacks the magma blasts were resisted/absorbed (only had fire res aura for my fire resistance). As long as i stayed above 50% while on Rag when the adds came out BoS brought mana up and SoL brought hp up then I was ready to go all out on Rag some more.\r\n\r\nMost important thing that I haven't seen in previous posts, use a BoA weapon! They don't take durability damage and since the fight only lasted 20 mins I'd say they are more than enough damage to be worth not having to pay repair bills on 2 dead weapons", "date": "2010-07-02T19:16:09-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 1076308, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tigerarmy666", "body": "Just duo'd this with a bm hunter and enh shammy. \r\n\r\n Popped all cds and went for a quick burn with the hunter pet tanking. I (shammy) ended up spending most of my time chain healing the pet since rags immune to fire damage. Really annoying as enhance. Easily doable though, happy hunting.", "date": "2010-07-08T19:56:20-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1077684, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "153992", "body": "Solo'd as an 80 Blood DK with iLevel gear no more than 226. \r\n\r\nI had all four pieces of fire resistance gear from Badges of Justice and used a Lesser Flask of Resistance to give me a total of 250 fire resist. I also threw on some pieces of tank gear to make up for the stamina loss, netting me about 24k health.\r\n\r\nIt was a pretty easy fight with two close calls due to fall damage. A cycle of Anti-Magic Shell + Rune Tap and Vampiric Blood + Rune Tap (with Icebound Fortitude thrown in every now and then) kept me healthy while and after getting knocked up. I blew whatever remaining cooldowns I had including Death Pact when the Sons spawned. I didn't keep track of how long it had taken but I would estimate no more than 15 minutes, most likely less.", "date": "2010-07-10T19:32:49-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1085855, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "droodlet", "body": "Remember, he will dissapear after about 2 hours dont go afk like me ^^", "date": "2010-07-21T12:34:40-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1096253, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "FailTrain", "body": "Managed to solo him with ease today as a protection paladin, never dropping below 90% HP. The fight took about 30 minutes. With Ragnaros' defeat, I have finally soloed every boss in Molten Core.\r\n\r\nThe gear I used was a mix between Fire Resistance-, tanking- and healing-items. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/compare?items=30767.0.3222:50991.0.0.0.40138.40119.40119:30766.0.2584:30768.0.1075:50313.0.3840:47733.0.3840:50356:48724:36271.-32.3816:50211:47698.0.3837.0.40119:18811.0.1354:30769.0.3297:47570.0.3850.0.40119:42948.0.2568:49835.0.1071:47661]Here[/url] I've listed them in the comparison tool, along with enchants and gems. As I had earlier wiped during attempts at soloing Ragnaros because of fall damage, I planned to equip some healing gear so I could easily heal back to full when I'd take fall damage next time. The libram is probably the only item that's equipped only for extra damage. This gear-setup gave me a whopping 460 Fire Resistance (giving me the resistance rating \"Excellent\", never seen that before) when combined with Fire Resistance Aura. Using a [i]Bind on Account[/i]-weapon as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/user=ludafrank]ludafrank[/url] suggested (thanks man!) I also avoided Ragnaros' [i]Melt Weapon[/i]-ability.\r\n\r\nFollowing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/user=Artharas]Artharas[/url]' tip (thanks to you too!) by standing [url=http://img100.imageshack.us/img100/8962/placement.jpg]here[/url], I noticed I had enough resistance to walk down in the lava, right up to Ragnaros. This increased the \"safe\" distance at which Ragnaros could knock me back with. \r\n\r\nHealing turned out to be a lot easier than I had expected. [i]Divine Plea[/i] supplied me with all the mana I needed, and [i]Judgement of Light[/i] kept me at full HP almost the entire fight. I never had to use any other kind of heal (not [i]Lay on Hands[/i] either) nor [i]Divine Shield[/i]. My position when fighting Ragnaros always ensured that I fell in the lava when he knocked me back, and his adds were a joke. \r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/talent#sV0bZV0tAruMbsIufdE0z:jpGcmV]This[/url] is the talent build I used. It's a special (permanently in-test) \"soloing-build\" I created. Can always be improved... \r\n[b]<EDIT:>[/b] As of the upcoming expansion of Cataclysm, the talent calculators on wowhead and Blizzard's official sites have been reconfigured. Thus, this link no longer redirect to the build I used when I fought Ragnaros. There are various calculators which still uses the old talents, but as these will soon be outdated (and already somewhat are, even before Cataclysm), I see no point in listing the build I used anymore. \r\n\r\nThese are the buffs and items I used on myself: \r\n - Runescroll of Fortitude (+165 stamina)\r\n - Fish Feast (+80 Attack Power, 46 Spell Power and 40 Stamina)\r\n - Scroll of Strength VIII (+30 strength)\r\n - Elixir of Greater Agility (+25 agility, got a lot of them from a friend that leveled alchemy)\r\n - Seal of Vengeance\r\n - Fire Resistance Aura\r\n - Righteous Fury (-6% damage taken via talents)\r\n - Greater Blessing of Sanctuary\r\n\r\nOther buffs that were nearly permanently active: \r\n - Sacred Shield\r\n - Divine Plea\r\n - Holy Strength (+200 strength, from the Libram proc)\r\n\r\nAs healing was no problem I guess I could have swapped out some of the healing-items with my regular tanking gear. My math is too bad (at least too slow) to figure out whether the extra Spell Power boosted my Sacred Shield better than the strength from my tanking gear via the [i]Touched by the Light[/i]-talent.", "date": "2010-08-05T14:41:45-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-16T09:27:28-05:00", 3, "FailTrain"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1097766, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "614989", "body": "Soloed this morning with my buddy's Ret pally 2843 gs average icc gear. \r\nWent in killed the council took my chances against rag.... died from fall damage cause i stood in the wrong place. then i moved to the southeast and when he knocked back i would land on the rock, heal, and continue the onslaught. fire res aura helps a lot and i always had AoW active for emergency heals so dps was a lil low (only about 4k-5k dps). The only time i had to use a CD was divine shield the second time the sons came up. i was on the rock at the time and was automatically teleported down and instead of taking on 4 or 5 at a time i had ALL of them and i wasn't prepared cause i had just taken a bit of fall damage, but i survived and divine stormed my way out of there. Eventually he came up I burned him some more and that was the end of it.\r\n97g 2 boe blues, judgment legs (WOOT!) warrior legs, crap trinket and a cloak were my rewards for downing him! sent the boes to my toons and let him have the epics for repair. very much worth it for a weekly farm.", "date": "2010-08-09T07:29:33-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I just soloed him on my ret pally, was wearing near full relentless, and it was a breeze, one of the easiest in the instance. Like mentioned earlier, if u stand at a specific location, facing him, he will knock u back onto a jagged rock, i would give the coordinates, but im writing this after i teleported to gadgetzan =/ .   I used Seal of Corruption, BoM, and JoL on him, and switched to Seal of Command when killing adds. Diddnt have to use any Cd's, but be mindful of your hp when he spawns adds, as they will drop your hp alot faster than Rag himself. Also, to add some info, I forgot to repair", "creationdate": "2010-08-09T07:29:34-05:00", "id": 456745, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1097766, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ilCorvo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1107713, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "609112", "body": "Soloing this as deathknight was pretty easy, once i found the right spot to stand on, so the knockback makes me land into the lava and not land, cause the falldmg is whats going to kill you, Also if u dont get to him fast enough he will do 5k+ fire dmg every few secs on you.\r\n\r\nYou should be in blood spec ofc with tanking gear on, and use blood tap or other defensive abilitys right after he hes knockbacked you and he does hes 5k fire dmg on you cause your out of range of hes melee. The adds that spawn on 75% and 25% hp was a joke(think its more then 2 times it spawns but not sure when)\r\n\r\nThis fight took me 35 mins.\r\n\r\nAlso a sidenote for paladin's make sure if your there alone to take with you a spare weapon,been there 2 times on my palladin so far and my weapon broke both times, did not have this problem as deathknight though..\r\n\r\nDont know if there is many people soloing this for the Eye drop, but my guess is there is a few, hope this helps, gonna upload picture of the spot i found was best to stand at to avoid fall damage", "date": "2010-08-25T13:10:29-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1110834, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "146451", "body": "Just soloed him as a pure fury warrior. I picked up bloodthirst glyph and used lesser flask of resistance (with an additional +40 resistance with mixology) and had drums of kings and wild to bring my resistance up to 144. I also had to respec into improved intercept since all his knock ups came every 20 secs or so.\r\n\r\nI was able to get him down before the submerge but it was pretty close. Wouldn't recommend it unless you're very geared. My warrior is at 6500gs with shadowmourne. Pretty nice and quick for farming. \r\n\r\nWas also able to do most of the other bosses as fury except for Golemagg and Garr.", "date": "2010-08-30T05:45:57-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1123295, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "663952", "body": "I just soloed this guy on my warrior with a prot/fury spec with Bloodthirst, improved intercept and generic prot talents. Usual bloodthirst, Enraged Regen, and Cleave glyphs. Just under 40k with my tank gear (5300ish gs) and nothing special (IE no fire resist gear or BC junk) I used Flask of resist, Drums of kings and wild, Runescroll and food to hit about 47-48k with commanding shout.\r\n\r\nI must say Improved Intercept is  MUST. His knockback is on a 22-25 sec cooldown it seemed and without the talent you would get killed pretty quick with his instant pwn you for not being in melee ability. He calls it out...so I would start mashing my intercept button so I could get it off with the weird distance of being knocked up+out. I can't express enough how important this was for me for the fight. You have the Last stand+engraged regen O sh!t button but you can't use it very often. Nail the intercepts you should be fine.\r\n\r\nI had to fight in beserker stance the whole time due to latency and macros to switch to berserker and cast Intercept not being 100% effective. Wasn't bad though, glyphed Bloodthirst would outheal his damage over time. His dot hurts and will do more then you can heal through but it is on a cooldown and bloodthirst will catch up over the course of the fight. \r\n\r\nHe submerged about 4-5 times and I used that time to make sure I bloodthirsted up to 100%. \r\n\r\nMy weapon was broken about 20% and I had to switch to Bryn'toll for the last 20% but it was fine.\r\n\r\nI might try Bryn'toll for the whole fight next time to cut down on kill time, and switch to sword/shield on the sons. But either way, I would recommend an heirloom weapon or multiple weapons in your bags.\r\n\r\nTook  19 mins and 45 sec to down him. No Eye either :( \r\n\r\nMaybe next week. :)", "date": "2010-09-19T17:48:38-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 1149890, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Loktarn", "body": "As of 4.0.1, MC is totally soloable as a prot pally. I did ragnaros with about T9 gear+. In the last quarter of the fight, my weapon broke so I had to finish him with Judgement + Avenger's shield.\r\n\r\nUsed divine shield at least twice and many time Divine Protection. Word of Glory is a must for this.\r\n\r\nI did it in 12 minutes. Long, stressful and repetitive xD But worth the 140g he drop at the end.", "date": "2010-10-21T23:59:35-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 110, "id": 1150962, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "seitori", "body": "Pretty easy solo for Blood DK after 4.0.  I don't have the best gear; my average ilvl is 206 according to my stats.  That's with three FR greens on, ending up with 176 FR flasked total and just over 35k HP.  \r\n\r\nKey to this fight is being in the right position to avoid taking fall damage (and don't be afraid to toe the lava when in melee with Rags), and saving defensive CDs for the Sons.  A DK with my gear should actually be able to burn down the Sons quickly enough that you may even be able to use that phase of the fight for some downtime, saving one spawn alive so you can Rune Tap and Death Strike it to top yourself off.  \r\n\r\nAnother tip for this fight, even more cementing Blood as an ideal spec for it: after the knockback, Rags won't nuke you if there's something in melee range he can swing at.  This includes your ghoul or even a Bloodworm.  Sometimes it's hard to tell, but if you are going to get nuked instead, make sure you manage your CDs appropriately.  Try to alternate Bone Shield and AMS with each knockback.  \r\n\r\nAll in all, an easy chunk of change if you've got the gear or the skill for Gehennas.  Cores will continue to sell well, too.", "date": "2010-10-23T06:45:48-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 111, "id": 1151602, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "26852", "body": "I found a use for Subtlety as a Rogue...it makes Ragnaros soloable. The largest source of damage you will take is, [i]by far[/i], the 5k damage nuke he casts on you if no one is in melee range. So, go subtlety, but glyph more or less like a combat rogue, mash sinister strike, and just shadowstep back to him whenever he does the knockback. Didn't even need a repair bot, he dies long before my weapons were even close to broken.", "date": "2010-10-23T22:18:16-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also soloable as Assasination, ilevel 264 gear, specced into Deadened Nerves and Improved Recuperate. I used two pieces of TBC blue fire res gear and a resistance flask for a total of 120 fire res, could have done it with less probably. Just kept up Recuperate and used CoS or Sprint as cooldowns permitted to get back after a knockback. The Sons of Flame showed up around 15% but they were no problem.", "creationdate": "2010-11-10T11:45:09-06:00", "id": 191498, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1151602, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rana", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 1152813, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vaugn", "body": "I just solo'ed Molten Core as a discipline priest.  Interestingly, I died several times on trash but never on a boss.  I have 264 gear and used a disc pvp spec (for the extra dps from spell reflection).  Archangel is a must for mana regeneration.\r\n\r\nA few notes in no particular order.\r\n\r\n-- Ragnaros's adds are far more challenging than he is, and because of Rag's 1.1 million hit points you'll need to go through several waves of adds.  The adds' combined dps is easily enough to take out a disc priest if you're not careful.  I used power infusion + holy nova spam for a while, but when I dropped to 50% health, I'd fear then focus my dps on the remaining adds near me.  They only have 15k health each and have usually dropped about half from the holy nova spam, so they die fairly quickly.  Hint: fight on the NE side of Ragnaros so you get tossed back into lava, not onto land.\r\n\r\n-- The big fire elemental trash (firelords?  I don't recall their name) are quite a pain.  The have a 15 second silences which is an absolute killer. Not to mention their adds begin splitting.  The adds have a large pile of health each, so it takes a while to get them down (which leaves others to split in the meantime).  I generally focused all my dps on the fire lord and got out my shadowfiend for extra dps as soon as possible, then focused on the adds.  Mostly though you can avoid these guys.\r\n\r\n-- I thought Garr would be more difficult than he was.  I pulled by DOT'ing up a few adds but mostly did my damage through holy nova spam.  Power Word: Shield worked surprisingly well in spite of Garr's dispel magic, as they'd beat through it fairly quickly anyway.\r\n\r\n-- Geddon was a joke.  I fought him in the tunnel to avoid being tossed very high in the air.\r\n\r\n-- Golemagg wasn't too tough, although he did hit rather hard once he was enraged.  I pulled out my shadowfiend after his enrage then cast fade so I could focus my attacks without needing as much healing.  They killed the shadowfiend rather quickly though, so in retrospect I might have been better off serving as a tank while letting the shadowfiend dps Golemagg instead.\r\n\r\n-- Sulfuron's healers hit surprisingly weakly.  I mana burned them outta mana then blew 'em away one by one.  E-Z.\r\n\r\n-- Majordomo's adds were something of a pain, as I had him and eight adds on me at once.  That means their dps drops during the fight though, so don't be afraid to burn your cooldowns earlier on.  (It's an 8-10 minute fight anyway).  I mana burned the healers out of mana (doesn't take long) then pulled out my shadowfiend and focus'ed one down.  From there on it was just a matter of killing the healers one by one, then the other adds.  All in all, not difficult.  Just time-consuming and requiring a bit of concentration.\r\n\r\n-- Shazzrah has a -75% healing curse on you during the fight.  Rather annoying, but you can heal through it anyway (if not very efficiently).  I spent a lot of time ducking out of his flamestorm, but in restrospect I might have been served just sitting through it so I could nuke him down faster.\r\n\r\nOverall, a very fun experience.  I was surprised I was able to do it.  Quite fun, and an enjoyable challenge for the bored discipline priest.", "date": "2010-10-25T11:34:00-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 113, "id": 1156496, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "430501", "body": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oju6cjG3vJM the most epic ragnaros kill evah", "date": "2010-10-30T01:56:37-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 114, "id": 1157783, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chimeling", "body": "Just completed the whole Molten Core as a retri paladin, apart from Golemagg the Incinerator (that guy is a total d-bag, the fight took 33minutes as a holy paladin).\n\nRagnaros is simple, stand by his feet, when he throws you away, give yourself a quick heal, the fall damage can be as high as 50% of your max. hp - as for the adds, get 3 holy power, divine storm, rinse & repeat until they're only 3-4 left, then Word of Glory yourself up to max hp.\n\n\nChimeling @ Sunstrider EU.", "date": "2010-10-31T16:14:16-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-31T16:14:37-05:00", 1, "Chimeling"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 1165856, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "darkphoenix2012", "body": "Just wanted to let everyone that know that the new Ragnaros encounter has the dialog sounds available in the same place where the old ones were.  You can extract these sounds using an MPQ extractor.  These sounds belong to blizzard so please do not abuse them in any way.  I thought people who were excited to see ragnaros come back might appreciate this, beware spoiler alert.", "date": "2010-11-08T22:51:24-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 1170263, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kaze950", "body": "Just solo'd as a hunter, not too difficult. Was BM using spirit beast, no t5. The heal comes in handy for the knockbacks where he'll aggro onto you for a few seconds. The real trick is just killing him before add phase. He died in 117 seconds for me.\r\n\r\nSo, if any hunters out there are interested for tier 1/petrified leaf/rep, MC is soloable.", "date": "2010-11-13T20:07:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
