{"commentv2": 1, "number": 162, "id": 1460100, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "orcsmash", "body": "I died while soloing him and when I returned executus was back to life and rag was still there, so after I killed rag I was able to summon and kill another one. If this happens to you don't talk to executus before you kill the first one or you might have to deal with two Ragnaroses at once.", "date": "2011-07-04T07:59:09-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Sort of same thing happened to me, i killed the first rag, and majordomo spawned, so i killed 2. DOUBLE RAGNAROS IN THE MOLTEN FRONT SKY, IT'S A BEAUTIFUL SIGHT.", "creationdate": "2011-07-04T12:31:48-05:00", "id": 250066, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1460100, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xenosin123", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-04T08:02:22-05:00", 1, "orcsmash"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 163, "id": 1461981, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "845677", "body": "I solo'd this guy on my 85 DK, for kicks and for the achievement.\r\n\r\nThought it would be easy until I realized Wrath sent you skyward (or cave-ceiling-ward if you wanna be technical) and I would lose 60% of my HP from falling damage. After that horrible death, I tried again. Do note that I had no means of falling speed reductions (i.e. parachute) on me at the time so I had to scope the lava for a deep enough pool that would cushion my fall, I found one and was able to down Raggy the first time... however, something miraculous happened. Executus, who summons him, respawned again while Raggy stayed after I rezzed and came in again. I downed him twice in 1 day! Sadly, no Eye dropped on either occasions. Got a solid 300g from those 2 fights alone (minus the 50g required to repair my badly melted weapon.)", "date": "2011-07-06T00:27:32-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed.  I've been soloing Rag for the past few weeks now for Hydraxian Waterlords rep and also noticed Executus respawned last time I tried, which granted me additional rep and loot.  May be a \"feature\" introduced in 4.2.  [b]Update:[/b] Executus no longer respawns, so it is no longer possible to kill Rag twice.", "creationdate": "2011-07-07T13:33:06-05:00", "id": 250802, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1461981, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mcmagi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The falling damage can be easily avoided on a warrior, and probably other classes too.  If timed right you can intercept whilst mid air, and you can also Heroic Leap if you have your camera angle set right, this trick also works for Baron Geddon's \"Living Bomb\".", "creationdate": "2011-08-24T06:35:29-05:00", "id": 260353, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1461981, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "866854", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 164, "id": 1463344, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Malfious", "body": "No longer immune to fire damage as of 4.2", "date": "2011-07-07T08:49:56-05:00", "rating": 44, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also noticed that, was wondering if 2pc bonus is going to do anything to him. He seems to have no fire resistance at all now (apparently along with all mobs in the instance). Would be funny if they added all the fire damage as set bonuses and actually made FL bosses immune to it ;p", "creationdate": "2011-08-15T06:27:19-05:00", "id": 258689, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1463344, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Iroared", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 165, "id": 1465431, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "716725", "body": "Typical as with all vanilla raids and instances,\r\nthe last boss always seems the easyiest.\r\n\r\nSoloed this boss and all other bosses in Molten Core \r\nas a Destruction Lock with hardly and problems, \r\nDied once cause could not be bothered to wait for a cooldown.\r\n\r\nAnyways to summon this boss all the other bosses in this raid MUST be destroyed,\r\nThen goto [npc=12018 domain=www] \r\nKill all of his gaurds and he will surrender (Do NOT try to kill him just kill his gaurds)\r\nthen he will tell you to meet him near where,\r\n[npc=11502 domain=www] spawns\r\nTalk to him and bingo final boss will spawn after a short conversation.\r\n\r\nGood Luck", "date": "2011-07-09T13:02:15-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-09T13:03:12-05:00", 1, "716725"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 166, "id": 1489813, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wowpixel", "body": "Soloed the entire MC raid instance as a Holy paladin (yes, lowest DPS sub-class!). Killed Rag in less than 7mins in complete Healadin gear (ilevel 359/378). So any class now can solo MC with zero deaths, too.", "date": "2011-08-08T03:53:41-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 167, "id": 1494843, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rederoin", "body": "Just a note to the hunters(and maybe warlocks).\r\n\r\nRagnaros only punts your pet(if he has aggro), not you.\r\nSo, no need to worry about finding the \"sweet spot\".", "date": "2011-08-14T11:36:04-05:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 168, "id": 1496609, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "866114", "body": "A pain to heal for. As a druid i was required to Battle Rez one of our top DPS and i had a difficulty getting to his body because he kept tossing me off to a random direction.\n\nEasy boss. was disapointed with the drops. Definately going for Hand of Rag on my Pally.", "date": "2011-08-16T21:54:32-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-08-16T21:55:03-05:00", 2, "866114"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 169, "id": 1497172, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Slayman", "body": "It depends on your phone, but these steps are the groundwork:\r\nGet an [u]MPQ extractor software (MPQ Editor might work)[/u]\r\nnavigate inside the sound.MPQ to \\Creature\\Ragnaros\\\r\nonce there look for the files Spicbringer picked in the above post:\r\n[quote]\"By fire be purged!\"\r\n\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSpecialAttack01.wav\r\n\r\n\"Taste the flames of Sulfuron!\"\r\n\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSpecialAttack02.wav\r\n\r\n\"My patience is dwindling! Come, gnats, to your death!\"\r\n\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSpecialAttack03.wav\r\n\r\n\"Die, insects!\"\r\n\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosSlay01.wav\r\n\r\nNasty sounds( Aka raggy dies):\r\n\\\\Creature\\\\Ragnaros\\\\RagnarosDeath.wav[/quote]\r\n[i](ignore the double slashes, those are for escaping on another when executing inside of WoW)[/i]\r\nwith said Editor simply extract those .wav files.\r\n.wav is an uncompressed soundfile, and basically everything can play it, some phones may need it to be converted however (i.e. iPhone)\r\nOnce you have the files get them on your phone, as mentioned above that procedure is different for every phone and if you google for that you should be good.", "date": "2011-08-17T15:57:37-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 170, "id": 1498503, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "866854", "body": "Downed Rag in just over a minute on my warrior. Too easy.", "date": "2011-08-19T10:35:59-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 171, "id": 1511730, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "544077", "body": "It appears he's no longer immune to fire, did this today as an Enhancement Shaman, and recount shows no damage resisted, my previous times here, my lava lash and flame shock had been useless, but they seem to do full damage now.  I don't recall seeing it in any patch notes though.\n\nEdit: I'm still killing him every week on my shaman, he's still not fire immune... idk why this is getting downrated....", "date": "2011-09-06T23:09:32-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It also may be worth noting that he DOES still have negative frost resistance.", "creationdate": "2011-09-06T23:11:03-05:00", "id": 262934, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1511730, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "544077", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-10-16T18:26:36-05:00", 1, "544077"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 172, "id": 1519066, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "851942", "body": "With the impending 4.3, I picked up farming MC for Rogue gear.(Mainly wanted the daggers and BF legs but also collectting Nightstalker) The entire zone is a pretty easy solo. Granted I am in high dps PvE gear, I'm still sure I could easily do it in my V10 PvP gear; kills would just take longer.\r\n\r\nI stealth past all the trash except the occasional dogs that detect me, and gank bosses. They're pretty easy fights and struggle just to beat through improved Recuperate. I use Evasion on the ones with large groups of trash, by the time my 20sec evade runs out they've all died to FoK spam and the boss follows shortly. There isn't much else to say, they're too easy to give strategy. I will say that I learned to point Ragnaros a certain direction so that I land on the ground after punts... that's about it. I could also suggest using Cloak on Baron's bomb debuff to avoid being sky tossed, but it'll only work 1 time and he'll get off 3-4 bombs if you're solo. On Gar and the others with adds just spam FoK with Evasion.\r\n\r\nI also 2man BWL weekly with a guildmember and am starting up SSC/Eye raids too. We all want our fancy T5 and weapons for next patch. At the time of this post I am 6/8 Nightstalker 4/8 Bloodfang 2/5 Deathmantle. Whichever set I can fill up by the time 4.3 hits will likely be the winner.(I hope it's Deathmantle because that one made a killer PvP set once upon a time and I'd love to wear it for that cause. Ganking players with skull mask and hood=win)\r\n\r\nDon't wait until afterwards to start getting cool models... you can farm them right now in advance and have them just waiting for day 1 of the patch. I also recommend this if you want PvE sets because you will likely have to do them 5-10 times to get all the pieces and it's only 1 clear per week. I've done MC and BWL 5 times each(That's 5 weeks) and you see they still aren't done. 5 clears of BWL and I'm still missing the hat, shoulder, gloves, boots(Aka the slots of actual value refusing to drop). I'd seriously have regretted not farming in advance.", "date": "2011-09-16T02:30:56-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 173, "id": 1519128, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheRealLink", "body": "Been giving this guy a go lately for the past few days and I think I'm just not quite there gear-wise yet.  Tried the following all with some success (all in battle stances):\r\n\r\n1.  Nightelf Pure Fury Warrior (with a couple points in Arms and Protection) @ 83, Titan's Grip, and enhanced Bloodthirst / Regeneration bonuses (my normal setup).  No fire resist though.  Figured out how to at least land on the high cliff but can't figure out for the life of me if I can use charge at all while being thrown; it seems to be not at all despite everyone seemingly to say the contrary.  Had no to minor problems with the other bosses but was able to defeat them all except Ragnaros so far.\r\n2.  Respeced into Arms/Fury with that enhanced charge to hit it in the air - that helped a lot!  Seems like I take more damage though with Arms spec.\r\n3.  Arms/Fury boosted from 0 FR up to ~108 Fire Resist\r\n4.  Tried all three of above combinations with 2H+Shield, 2H alone or 1H+Shield...  Seems like the order of best damage I could do was 1H+Shield Fury or Arms, 2H+Shield Fury, and then just plain old 2H with the Arms tree active.  \r\n5.  Tried again with +FR and one of those Darkmoon Cards giving a small heal boost when hitting in melee.  It helped slightly but of course no where near enough.\r\n---(edit)\r\n6.  Purchased a Mending scroll for my weapon.  It helped enough to notice some fight longevity but not enough to counteract his damage.\r\n7.  Likewise tried a Windwalker scroll - that too gave some avoiding damage but not quite enough.\r\n8.  Put an enchantment on every piece of armor I had... helped a little.\r\n9.  Tried a few Golem potions.  Again, nice damage output but not enough.\r\n\r\nGreatest success so far is pretty much the order listed, though the amounts don't vary by too much... I can get him down to the 700's (finally got into 670s on my last try) but nothing close enough to beat him down yet.  Using pot and regeneration but that's pretty much it for healing regardless of setup.  ilevel is about 310.\r\n\r\nJust not sure if I'm geared up enough just yet.  The few warriors posting so far haven't said their levels except for I think, the one 80... I'd imagine I'd be able to kill him at 85 though I hope.  Not saying he's *supposed* to be easy after all but I just wonder if there's something I'm doing \"wrong\".\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nFrom the later attempts with focusing on pure defense (1H, Shield, FR), damage (2H, Golem Pot, no FR), or healing (1 or 2H, FR, Mending) I've gotten him consistently down into the 600s.  With mending, I finally hit the upper 400s so getting there ;).  \r\n\r\nAfter every possible combo I can think of, I think I'll simply have to return and try this again at 84 or 85.  Since those two levels continue to offer huge health boosts and recoveries (regeneration), I would think it's doable at 85.", "date": "2011-09-16T04:55:06-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-09-17T02:56:51-05:00", 1, "TheRealLink"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 174, "id": 1520672, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "bradb", "body": "Soloed Raggy with my frost mage (352 ilvl) with no problems. He was quite possibly the easiest boss to solo in Molten Core. I stood underneath the rock formation as one usually would, applied [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=543]mage armor[/url] and glyphed [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=7302]frost armor[/url] (which could have been replaced by something else, it obviously wasn't needed and engaged him, using CDs. He didn't even knockback, he just cast his Magma Blast. His negative frost resistance may have helped, though I have my doubts that he even still has it.\r\n\r\nWas a very profitable raid to solo for a frost mage considering the small amount of effort you have to put in.\r\n\r\nRecorded it, [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6J3Sajt-0fU]here's the video[/url].", "date": "2011-09-18T06:27:37-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What do I need to make Ragnaros appear ?", "creationdate": "2011-11-07T18:46:27-06:00", "id": 276306, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1520672, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346483", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "To make Ragnaros appear, you must defeat all of the other bosses first.    I personally ran into this problem after I saw that Majordomo wasn't where he was supposed to be on the map.  I went directly for Golemagg, downed him, and ran into Rag's room, and nothing.  Turns out Majordomo spawned after I downed Golemagg.  Hope this helps!", "creationdate": "2011-11-12T03:32:37-06:00", "id": 277233, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1520672, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Foltzy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 175, "id": 1522197, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Blacky22", "body": "Defeated without any help with my protect pala lvl 83 at second try ( first died because the falling damage, if you want to avoid it, you must stay at the point where some lava is next to ragnaros)\r\nSo proud of it :D", "date": "2011-09-19T22:11:47-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Why is this being downrated?", "creationdate": "2011-12-09T03:24:25-06:00", "id": 285415, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1522197, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Blacky22", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 176, "id": 1529199, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "genshou", "body": "Solo'd as an ilvl 351 blood death knight. If you happen to get knocked up in the air, having the Path of Frost glyph that lessens fall damage is VERY helpful. Otherwise, a pretty straightforward fight.", "date": "2011-09-27T22:45:59-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 177, "id": 1567090, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "761515", "body": "Just solo'd him as an 85 Gnomish Fury Warrior with 328 item level.\r\nAfter 2 initial wipes I got scared and went and got a prismatic elixir for resistance and a small food buff (90stam/90str)\r\nIn general it was fairly easy, just required some spot on timing. I just burned him down with bloodthirst constantly and using intercept immediately after his \"Wrath of Ragnaros\". \r\nThe hardest part was in fact timing intercepts since it's a very small window in which you can actually use it. I actually missed a few of the intercepts due to either cooldown or just bad timing, the first one dealt me a massive 60k fall damage(ouch!) but I was lucky with the other ones as I landed in the lava. I popped Frenzied Regeneration after the 60k hit and bloodthirst wound up keeping me alive throughout the rest of the fight.\r\nI hit the 3 minute timer when he was around 150k hp and after clearing out his children(?) it was fairly simple to just spam execute and bloodthirst and shame his ego.\r\n\r\nAll in all it was VERY exciting! While I may not say, EVER, want to solo him again I can say it was a fun thing to try :D", "date": "2011-11-09T00:00:16-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 178, "id": 1570044, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheRealLink", "body": "Came back and downed him today ;).  Level 85 Arms Warrior with Inpatience of Youth from Tol Barad, a Golem Blood Potion, and the Tol Barad 2H Sword with the usual pot and Enraged Regeneration.  Kept getting him between 250-500K without any fire resist so added 100 points' worth (despite it horribly affecting my gear), and added a mending buff to help migrate the time to cycle ER.  ilevel was in the upper 330s / low 340s so not even near maxed out.\n\nThankfully, I could use ER and Bladestorm right as the sons came up and I had 10K HP left!  From there just executed as fast as I could.  For my troubles I got a few purples, blues, and 137 gold.", "date": "2011-11-12T02:53:31-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-11-12T02:54:41-06:00", 1, "TheRealLink"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 179, "id": 1570308, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rageahol", "body": "Just killed him as an arms warrior in s10 honor gear and Jeklik's smasher. VERY easy fight, I only used charge 3 times to get back down and didn't have to use any CDs.", "date": "2011-11-12T10:10:25-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 180, "id": 1577915, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "852901", "body": "I guess people don't like comments on how others solo'ed Ragnaros.\nOn another note, he has a swirly lower half in Molten Core like Al'akir and Neptulon do in Cataclysm, but I guess only him and Therazane get to experience having feet in Cata.", "date": "2011-11-21T20:39:23-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-11-21T20:47:33-06:00", 2, "852901"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 181, "id": 1600408, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "924697", "body": "Soloed him with my DK. Whenever he used Wrath of Ragnaros, though, I got knocked into the lava, every time, so fall damage wasn't that much of a deal. Dropped some tier epics and some world blues.\r\nI run through molten core weekly, not only for the right half of the bindings, but because it's fun and a way to kill boredom.", "date": "2011-12-22T15:43:29-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 182, "id": 1604132, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "727965", "body": "Any 80+ toon should be able to do this fight solo.  The only \"trick\" is to stand with your back to the widest part of the lava.  On the MC map here that is about 9 o'clock.  When you get knocked back, you will land in the lava and can swim back over to the boss.  Of course, if you are ranged dps class you can just sit back and burn.", "date": "2011-12-30T11:37:15-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "\"On the MC map here that is about 9 o'clock.\"This is a lie, you will land on the path for significant damage!I don't know what kind of clock this person uses but the widest part of the lava is in the 12 to 1 o'clock position. If you can;'t do adequate dps like some others have said he will spawn adds and you will die.", "creationdate": "2012-06-03T12:10:29-05:00", "id": 547534, "rating": -4, "commentid": 1604132, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "839525", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 183, "id": 1605447, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Surge479", "body": "I just want everyone who is wondering to know this boss can be soloed. I did it on my ilvl 377 Boomkin. The only thing to note is that Rag must be killed quickly otherwise he spawns adds and you can't handle them alone.", "date": "2012-01-01T21:30:53-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ran the instance last monday as a Holy paladin. Killed everything including the adds. Solo - ilevel 378 - 100% healadin gear - zero deaths. If a Holy can do it, a-n-y subclass can!", "creationdate": "2012-01-09T00:40:23-06:00", "id": 506460, "rating": -5, "commentid": 1605447, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wowpixel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 184, "id": 1605709, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "916115", "body": "The Firelord and his brethren once held sway over the entire world. As a servant of the Old Gods, he fought against the Titans for domination over the planet. The victorious Titans banished him and his brethren to the Elemental Plane \u2014 there to remain imprisoned until the end of time. It was then and there that the brothers turned on each other. For five millennia a battle was fought at the core of this world. It was during the Elemental Sundering that Ragnaros attacked Thunderaan, Prince of Air. Thunderaan was utterly defeated and the Firelord feasted upon his essence, but was unable to consume him entirely. Ragnaros divided what remained between his servants, Baron Geddon and Garr.\r\n\r\nIn the center of a vast lake of fire in the Elemental Plane stands Sulfuron Keep, the home of Ragnaros. Until comparatively recently, he ruled his underground land with a molten iron fist.\r\n\r\nAround three hundred years ago the ambitious and ruthless Dark Iron clan initiated a war against their dwarven brethren, the Bronzebeard clan and Wildhammer clan, thinking that they were about to unite against the Dark Irons. During this War of the Three Hammers, the Dark Iron dwarf leader named Thaurissan lay siege to the Bronzebeard's capital city of Ironforge, while his wife Modgud attacked the Wildhammer capital of Grim Batol. Mudgod was succesful in her assault upon the Wildhammer dwarves, but Thaurissan proved less succesful. The Bronzebeard dwarves repelled his attack and quickly dispatched aid to the Wildhammer dwarves. In a short time, the Dark Irons' fortunes took a turn for the worse, and they were pushed back to the city of Thaurissan, the Dark Iron dwarven home. Thaurissan, seeking to summon a supernatural minion that would turn the tide of the war back to his favor, called upon the ancient powers sleeping beneath the world. To Thaurissan's surprise, and ultimately his doom, the creature that emerged was more terrible than any nightmare he could have imagined.\r\n\r\nNow, freed by Thaurissan's call, Ragnaros erupted into being once again. Ragnaros' apocalyptic rebirth into Azeroth shattered the Redridge Mountains and created a raging volcano at the center of the devastation. The volcano, known as Blackrock Mountain, was bordered by what is now known as the Searing Gorge, to the north, and the Burning Steppes, to the south. Though Thaurissan was killed by the forces he had unleashed, his surviving Dark Iron clan brethren were ultimately enslaved by Ragnaros and his elementals. Many Dark Iron dwarves remain within the lower areas of the mountain, especially Blackrock Depths, toiling away at the behest of Ragnaros and the Firelord's lieutenants. They worship Ragnaros, considering him not only a Elemental Lord but also an Old God, although he is only affiliated with the Old Gods. The Bronzebeards and Wildhammers, however, remain free.\r\n\r\nWitnessing the horrific devastation and the fires spreading across the southern mountains, the Bronzebeards' King Madoran and Wildhammers' King Khardros halted their armies and hastily turned back towards their kingdoms, unwilling to face the awesome wrath of Ragnaros. Now he lies at the bottom of that volcano on Azeroth, striving to find a way home, as well as to gather his strength once again so he can burn away Azeroth and take it for his own. Meanwhile, in Sulfuron Keep and elsewhere across the Firelands, his elemental princes battle constantly for dominance. He and his dwarven minions took control of the Blackrock mountain's volcanic depths and made war on the orcs in the Upper Blackrock Spire, which served as the seat of power for Nefarian the black dragon. Ragnaros has uncovered the secret to creating life from stone and plans to build an army of unstoppable golems to aid him in conquering the whole of Blackrock Mountain.", "date": "2012-01-02T08:20:15-06:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 185, "id": 1608839, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wikkedhead", "body": "Killed him in 56s with my Enh Shaman (383).\r\n\r\nGot knocked back once.", "date": "2012-01-08T17:38:27-06:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 186, "id": 1630952, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "MABGamer6407", "body": "2 mand this as my 1 of my Marks main 85 Hunters and My Buddys 85 Ret Pally. My Croc Pet Kept Agro while we were able to whittle down his hp. He was a long yet simple Fight other then his \"Wrath of Ragnaros\" That knocked us Super far. killd My bud near the end so i had To Use Snappy (my croc) carefully as Tank But we got him not long after, we did't have much if any epics Prob in the \"330s\" item lv i think. Fun To go off an 2 man those old Raids an such.\n\nwhy this is down rated i don't know. im just trying to give advice on how i handled this place.", "date": "2012-02-23T23:39:57-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Probably because people have been 2 manning Ragnaros since Wrath. It's not really an achievement and you are not giving anyone with half a brain any real pointers or input.", "creationdate": "2012-08-09T10:50:26-05:00", "id": 562615, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1630952, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "331902", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-03-04T18:09:23-06:00", 1, "MABGamer6407"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 187, "id": 1673521, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "togahsisoka", "body": "Taking fall dmg no matter where I land...  Lava, land, cat form, bear form, it doesn't matter...  Could have sworn I solo'd him with worse gear...\n\nFinally found that if you melee approaching him from appoximately 3 o'clock (i.e. from his right) you can line up with a very high rock that you can land on when he tosses you.  Also note that you don't have to be right up on him to melee, you can be in the middle of the strip of land there and still hit him even though he seems far away.\n\nLanding in cat form helps if you're feral, but should still be doable.", "date": "2012-06-04T21:25:49-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Feral charge him as he flings you up in the air, should stop any fall damage completely.", "creationdate": "2012-06-10T15:24:16-05:00", "id": 549016, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1673521, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "800998", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "+ Warrior's Charge", "creationdate": "2013-05-26T06:42:38-05:00", "id": 662548, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1673521, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rastaroth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-06-05T07:59:27-05:00", 2, "togahsisoka"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 188, "id": 1686949, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "5241", "body": "Does anyone remember getting your entire guild the buffs from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=22888]Onyxia[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=24425/spirit-of-zandalar]Zul'Gurub[/url] (not to mention consumables) before your fullest attempts at Rag? I can remember the prep time being ridiculous just for one pull, and each attempt feeling like life or death...", "date": "2012-07-11T08:47:14-05:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "so you remember when the game was fun and challenging, I almost forgot about that", "creationdate": "2012-08-03T05:52:01-05:00", "id": 561284, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1686949, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "664366", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "So grinding for months on end for fire resist gear before you could even set foot in the place, then spending hours of preparation time for one pull was fun to you? You are either a troll or have serious rose tinted spectacles syndrome.", "creationdate": "2012-08-09T10:37:32-05:00", "id": 562611, "rating": 15, "commentid": 1686949, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "331902", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It wasn't fun, true, but the achievement of downing Ragnaros after a month worth of prep was something special that we no longer get in wow. Killing Deathwing leaves one with a \"well that's done\" feeling, killing Ragnaros with a group of 40 where everyone had to have gear and items to survive, let alone succeed was epic in every meaning of the word.", "creationdate": "2012-08-10T04:36:23-05:00", "id": 562772, "rating": 12, "commentid": 1686949, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TGFseb15", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The sense of accomplishment is no where near what it used to be. Truly epic feats in vanilla. Now its as TGFseb15 says, \"its over what next?\".", "creationdate": "2013-03-26T18:09:51-05:00", "id": 645761, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1686949, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "GreyMouser", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I think bc stuck a good balance between fun and challenge. Raids used to require at least some degree of preparation. These days you hit max level, grind heroics and then you're raid ready. And most raids people can knock out in no time at all.", "creationdate": "2014-06-22T08:48:18-05:00", "id": 752702, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1686949, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "soneil", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
