{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 1754066, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dothorio", "body": "Lil' Ragnaros currently has the highest in game power (374) of any level 25 battle pet.", "date": "2012-10-30T22:06:54-05:00", "rating": 60, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also of note, [url=npc=63370]Red Cricket[/url] comes in a close second with 371 and has an avoidance ability and a heal. After these two the next highest is a measly 357.", "creationdate": "2013-10-24T08:20:02-05:00", "id": 703413, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1754066, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Lucidic", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1788424, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "233270", "body": "This guy is severely OP.  Anyone know of any pets that are good against him?  Kinda sucks getting my butt handed to me by this guy lol\n\nEdit: why was I downrated because I asked a question and pointed out how strong he is?  I see nothing wrong with this post.", "date": "2012-12-28T01:06:29-06:00", "rating": 30, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Every attack he has is elemental, so critters (especially with Burrow-type spells) neutralize him a bit. But yes, he can potentially one-shot most non-rares with a Conflagrate crit if you set up with Scorched Earth from say, Murkablo. Hits like a truckload of trucks with everything.", "creationdate": "2013-02-14T16:40:28-06:00", "id": 632699, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1788424, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sturmreiter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Kun Lai Runt is a very good counter since Lil' Ragnaros is very slow. So Kun Lai Runt will stun him for 2 rounds and probably nuke him in his 3 hit combo", "creationdate": "2013-06-15T17:44:07-05:00", "id": 669365, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1788424, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "cessern", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Snails are the best, critter pet (less damage received) Aquatic abilities (more damage dealt), [url=http://www.wowhead.com/petability=449]self healing[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/petability=564]attack avoidance[/url]. Failing that, anything with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/petability=297]Pump[/url] is effective, crits WILL one-shot it. Also, he may hit the hardest of any rare level 25 pet, but he's also the slowest of any rare level 25 pet. You will be able to open first on him with any rare pet, so use that to your advantage.", "creationdate": "2013-08-22T08:58:14-05:00", "id": 686569, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1788424, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thecanman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I most agree with the above sugestion, try a Rapana Whelk. You can easily get them from the center marshy area of Dread Wastes. Probably there are some other places to catch them but that is where I remember seeing alot of them. Plus they are very high level so you can lvl up to 25 very quickly. Commentary on the abilities of snails is bang on the money btw!", "creationdate": "2014-02-18T03:16:44-06:00", "id": 729812, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1788424, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1037209", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-01-26T12:32:49-06:00", 1, "233270"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 1793405, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "223389", "body": "Is he Rare quality? I thought so but then I saw someone with a green / Uncommon one.", "date": "2013-01-06T01:11:09-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes he's rare quality. Sometimes if the person is currently in a pet battle, the pet they have out will show up as green to others, even if they are rare quality.", "creationdate": "2013-04-03T13:21:15-05:00", "id": 648055, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1793405, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zandy1990", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
